Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS,Chapter 1.12 - THEFT OR DAMAGE REWARD,1.12.010 - Authorized.,"Calaveras_County | Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS | Chapter 1.12 - THEFT OR DAMAGE REWARD | 1.12.010 - Authorized.
A reward of two hundred dollars will be paid for the furnishing of information leading to the apprehension and conviction of any person or persons of the theft of or the wilful and malicious destruction of or damage to any county property, including but not limited to roads, signs, equipment or buildings. (Ord. 955 § 1, 1978). ",Calaveras_County,10,Calaveras_County.pdf,73
Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS,Chapter 1.12 - THEFT OR DAMAGE REWARD,1.12.020 - Disputes—Total reward limited.,"Calaveras_County | Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS | Chapter 1.12 - THEFT OR DAMAGE REWARD | 1.12.020 - Disputes—Total reward limited.
In the case of disputes, the board of supervisors, after hearing the report and recommendation of the district attorney, shall be the sole judge of the party or parties entitled to receive any reward, and the total reward paid for any one offense or series of offenses shall not exceed two hundred dollars. (Ord. 955 § 2, 1978). ",Calaveras_County,10,Calaveras_County.pdf,72
Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS,Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS,,"Calaveras_County | Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS | Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS | 
Sections: Footnotes: --- (3) --- State Law reference— For statutory provisions on public work by prisoners in county jails, see Gov. Code § 25359 and Penal Code § 4017; for provisions on good behavior time credit, see Penal Code § 4019. ",Calaveras_County,10,Calaveras_County.pdf,59
Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS,Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS,1.16.010 - Use of prisoners for work bene␀ting county.,"Calaveras_County | Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS | Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS | 1.16.010 - Use of prisoners for work bene␀ting county.
Any, or all, male prisoners confined in the county jail under judgment of conviction of misdemeanor or as probationers, may be compelled to labor upon the public works, public grounds, roads, streets, alleys, highways or public buildings, or in such other places as may be deemed advisable in the county for the benefit of the county; provided that no prisoner shall be compelled to so labor who may be physically unable to do so, or whose safekeeping may be endangered thereby. The question of exemption from such labor for either cause mentioned shall be determined by the sheriff. ""Labor upon the public works,"" as used in this section, includes among other things clerical and menial labor in the county jail. (Ord. 604 § 1, 1971). ",Calaveras_County,10,Calaveras_County.pdf,156
Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS,Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS,1.16.020 - Guard—Appointment.,"Calaveras_County | Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS | Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS | 1.16.020 - Guard—Appointment.
Whenever there are, in the judgment of the sheriff, three or more prisoners in the county jail subject to labor, as provided in Section 1.16.010, the sheriff may appoint some suitable and responsible person as guard who shall discharge the duties of his position in person. Said guard shall be under the supervision of, and shall be responsible to, the sheriff. (Ord. 604 § 2, 1971). ",Calaveras_County,11,Calaveras_County.pdf,88
Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS,Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS,1.16.030 - Guard—Reception of prisoners—Work restriction.,"Calaveras_County | Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS | Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS | 1.16.030 - Guard—Reception of prisoners—Work restriction.
It is the duty of the guard provided for in Section 1.16.020 to receive from the sheriff, on each and every morning when the sheriff so orders, all the prisoners compelled to labor under this chapter, and it is the duty of the sheriff so to deliver them to the guard, and from the time they are delivered to the guard until they are returned to the county jail the guard shall be responsible for their safekeeping and custody; provided that no prisoner or prisoners shall be taken out by the guard, or be compelled to thus labor, on Sundays or legal holidays or at any time when the weather is so inclement as to be detrimental to the health of such prisoner or prisoners. (Ord. 604 § 3, 1971). ",Calaveras_County,11,Calaveras_County.pdf,154
Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS,Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS,1.16.040 - Hours of labor—Conveyance to and from place of labor.,"Calaveras_County | Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS | Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS | 1.16.040 - Hours of labor—Conveyance to and from place of labor.
The guard shall call for and receive, not later than eight a.m. each day, the prisoners which may be compelled to labor as provided in this chapter, enforce their conveyance to the place of labor as expeditiously as possible, and compel them to labor continuously from the time of their arrival at such place (except for one hour at noon for rest and lunch) to such hour of cessation from labor as will permit their return to the county jail at an hour not earlier than four forty-five p.m. and not later than five p.m. at which cessation said guard shall so return the prisoners; provided that labor may be discontinued during inclement weather at the option of the guard. (Ord. 604 § 4, 1971). ",Calaveras_County,11,Calaveras_County.pdf,153
Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS,Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS,1.16.050 - Lunch supplied at county expense.,"Calaveras_County | Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS | Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS | 1.16.050 - Lunch supplied at county expense.
The sheriff shall supply the prisoners with sufficient suitable food for lunch at the expense of the county. (Ord. 604 § 5, 1971). ",Calaveras_County,11,Calaveras_County.pdf,33
Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS,Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS,1.16.060 - Determination of place and manner of labor.,"Calaveras_County | Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS | Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS | 1.16.060 - Determination of place and manner of labor.
The labor provided for in this chapter shall be performed at such places and in such manner as the sheriff and board of supervisors, from time to time, direct. (Ord. 604 § 6, 1971). ",Calaveras_County,11,Calaveras_County.pdf,46
Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS,Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS,1.16.070 - Compensation prohibited.,"Calaveras_County | Title 1 - GENERAL PROVISIONS | Chapter 1.16 - PRISONERS—PUBLIC WORKS | 1.16.070 - Compensation prohibited.
No prisoner shall receive any compensation for his labor under this chapter. (Ord. 604 § 7, 1971). ",Calaveras_County,11,Calaveras_County.pdf,27
