Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.04 - BOARD OF SUPERVISORS,,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.04 - BOARD OF SUPERVISORS | 
Sections: Footnotes: --- (2) --- State Law reference— For statutory provisions requiring local legislative bodies to establish the time of their regular meetings, see Gov. Code § 54954. ",Calaveras_County,13,Calaveras_County.pdf,40
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.04 - BOARD OF SUPERVISORS,2.04.010 - Meetings.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.04 - BOARD OF SUPERVISORS | 2.04.010 - Meetings.
Regular meetings of the board of supervisors shall be held on the second and fourth Tuesdays of every month. The board may also add additional regular meeting dates when it adopts its annual meeting calendar. Regular meetings shall begin at 9:00 a.m., or at 8:00 a.m. if one or more closed sessions are scheduled, in the supervisors' chambers in Government Center at the County Seat in San Andreas. However, nothing contained in this section shall prevent the board of supervisors from holding special meetings, emergency meetings, or otherwise canceling, adjourning, continuing or changing the time or place of any particular meeting in any manner permitted by law. (Ord. 2906 § 1, 2006: Ord. 2825 § 1, 2005: Ord. 2789 § 1, 2004: Ord. 2650 § 1, 2001: Ord. 2632 § 1, 2000: Ord. 541 § 1, 1970). (Ord. No. 2994, § 1, 8-9-2011; Ord. No. 3163, § 1, 9-28-2021) ",Calaveras_County,14,Calaveras_County.pdf,252
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.04 - BOARD OF SUPERVISORS,2.04.020 - Training and orientation of supervisors-elect.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.04 - BOARD OF SUPERVISORS | 2.04.020 - Training and orientation of supervisors-elect.
A. Upon request of a supervisor-elect, county general fund moneys may be used prior to the assumption of office by that supervisor-elect, for the training and orientation of that supervisor-elect, including the payment of course fees, travel and per diem expenses, course materials and consultant fees. B. Such training and orientation programs, and expenses therefor, shall be those the board deems proper and beneficial to the exercise of supervisorial duties by newly elected supervisors. C. In order to receive training and orientation funds, the supervisor-elect shall make a formal request of the board of supervisors and comply with all requirements of the board. (Ord. 1536 § 1, 1982). ",Calaveras_County,14,Calaveras_County.pdf,142
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.06 - COUNTY CLERK-RECORDER,,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.06 - COUNTY CLERK-RECORDER | 
Sections: ",Calaveras_County,14,Calaveras_County.pdf,3
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.06 - COUNTY CLERK-RECORDER,2.06.010 - Assessor's parcel number.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.06 - COUNTY CLERK-RECORDER | 2.06.010 - Assessor's parcel number.
A. Every deed, instrument or writing by which lands, tenements or other realty in Calaveras County is sold, granted, assigned, transferred or otherwise conveyed shall have noted thereon its assessor's parcel number. The recorder shall not record any such deed, instrument or writing unless the assessor's parcel number is noted on it. The person who requests that such a document be recorded is charged with providing the recorder with the correct assessor's parcel number. B. The number required by this section shall be used solely for administrative and procedural purposes. It shall not constitute proof of title. In the event of conflicts, the stated legal description shall govern. C. The validity of any such deed, instrument or writing shall not be affected by the fact that the assessor's parcel number noted on it is erroneous or is omitted, and no liability shall attach to any person for such an error or omission. (Ord. 1742 § 1, 1985). ",Calaveras_County,14,Calaveras_County.pdf,199
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.08 - COUNTY COUNSEL,,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.08 - COUNTY COUNSEL | 
Sections: Footnotes: --- (3) --- State Law reference— For statutory provisions on county counsel, see Gov. Code § 27640 et seq. ",Calaveras_County,15,Calaveras_County.pdf,33
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.08 - COUNTY COUNSEL,2.08.010 - Established.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.08 - COUNTY COUNSEL | 2.08.010 - Established.
The position of county counsel is established under and pursuant to the terms and provisions of Section 27640 et seq. of the Government Code of the state. County counsel is appointed by the board of supervisors. As such, the county executive officer does not have the authority to employ, discipline, or dismiss county counsel. (Ord. 227 § 1, 1958). (Ord. No. 3194, § 1, 2-27-2024) ",Calaveras_County,15,Calaveras_County.pdf,98
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.08 - COUNTY COUNSEL,2.08.020 - Duty to act for public administrator—Fees.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.08 - COUNTY COUNSEL | 2.08.020 - Duty to act for public administrator—Fees.
A. In addition to such other duties as are prescribed by law, the county counsel shall act as attorney for the public administrator of the county in all estates in which the public administrator is appointed the executor, administrator with the will annexed, or administrator upon and after the fifth day of July, 1959, where the public administrator has priority for appointment as established by law. B. The public administrator may employ private counsel in those estates in which he is nominated and would not otherwise have priority, in those estates in which he is appointed administrator with the will annexed, or administrator pursuant to Chapter 6 (commencing with Section 480) of Division 3 of the Probate Code, and in those estates in which he is appointed administrator with will annexed for the reason the executor nominated in the will has refused to serve. C. In such matters where the county counsel furnishes representation, the county counsel shall collect the attorney's fees allowed by law and pay them into the county treasury. (Ord. 1045 § 7, 1978: Ord. 227 § 2, 1958). (Ord. No. 3194, § 1, 2-27-2024) ",Calaveras_County,15,Calaveras_County.pdf,249
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 
Sections: Footnotes: --- (4) --- Editor's note— Ord. No. 3184, § 1, adopted December 13, 2022, amended Chapter 2.10 in its entirety to read as herein set out. Former Chapter 2.10, §§ 2.10.005—2.10.110, pertained to the county administrative officer, and derived from Ord. No. 2941, 2008. ",Calaveras_County,15,Calaveras_County.pdf,96
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,2.10.010 - County executive o␀cer.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.010 - County executive o␀cer.
There shall be a county executive officer (CEO), who shall be the head of the administrative branch of the county government and act as the county's administrative officer pursuant to Govt. Code Section 24000(t). Where the term ""administrative coordinator,"" ""county administrative officer,"" or ""CAO"" is used in any county ordinance, resolution, regulation, or other county enactment, it shall be deemed to mean ""county executive officer."" (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,15,Calaveras_County.pdf,110
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,2.10.020 - Purpose.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.020 - Purpose.
The purpose of this chapter is to establish the position of county executive officer and to define the nature, duties, responsibilities, and delegated authority of the position. The CEO shall generally advise, assist, and act as agent for the board of supervisors, shall be responsible to the board for the proper and efficient administration of such affairs of the county that are placed in his or her charge by the board, and shall enforce ordinances, orders, and regulations as directed by the board. (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,16,Calaveras_County.pdf,116
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,2.10.030 - Appointment and removal.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.030 - Appointment and removal.
The CEO shall be appointed by and serve at the pleasure of the board of supervisors. He or she will be appointed by a majority vote of the board of supervisors and shall enter into a contract with the board which shall include provisions addressing length of tenure, removal, and notice. (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,16,Calaveras_County.pdf,77
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,2.10.040 - Quali␀cations.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.040 - Quali␀cations.
The CEO shall be chosen upon the basis of knowledge and skills in public administration, budgeting, personnel, and other relevant matters and shall have a combination of education and demonstrated experience to exhibit an ability to properly handle the breadth and depth of issues that face county government. These qualifications shall typically be met by a combination of educational training and management-level experience in public administration, fiscal management, and long-range planning. (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,16,Calaveras_County.pdf,103
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,2.10.050 - Salary and bene␀ts.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.050 - Salary and bene␀ts.
The salary and other compensation of the CEO shall be established by the board of supervisors and shall be paid by the auditor-controller in the same manner as the salaries and benefits of other county employees. (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,16,Calaveras_County.pdf,60
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,2.10.060 - General powers and duties.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.060 - General powers and duties.
The CEO shall be the chief administrative officer of the county, may head one or more departments, and shall be responsible to the board of supervisors for the proper administration of all affairs of the county. To that end, the CEO shall have the power and shall be required to: A. Supervise for the board of supervisors the administration of all county departments, offices, and institutions over which the board has responsibility and control. The CEO shall also act as the administrative officer for the board in administering all policies, procedures, departments, and institutions, including those departments in which the department head is an elected or appointed officer. B. Attend all meetings of the board of supervisors, unless excused therefrom, prepare matters for the board's consideration and action, and make recommendations to the board on matters within his/her authority. C. Coordinate development of the county's legislative platform and legislative advocacy efforts. D. Perform other such duties as may be required by the board of supervisors, not inconsistent with state or federal law or county code, and delegate functions to appropriate staff. E. Prepare and carry out administrative policies and procedures necessary to implement the directives, policies and goals established by the board relative to the operation of county government. F. It shall be the duty of each department head, elected or appointed, to provide information relating to the administrative operation of his/her department, upon request of the CEO, and to follow the administrative policies and procedures of the county. (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,16,Calaveras_County.pdf,312
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,2.10.070 - Budget matters.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.070 - Budget matters.
A. The CEO shall submit a proposed annual budget together with his/her recommendations to the board of supervisors for consideration and adoption. He/she shall supervise and direct preparation of the budget and review and evaluate all items including expenditures, revenues, and services. B. The CEO shall work closely with the county auditor-controller in the preparation and execution of the county's budget. C. After final adoption of the budget by the board of supervisors, the CEO shall administer the budget and exercise continuous expenditure control. He/she shall review all requests for appropriations and transfers and make recommendations to the board. He/she shall supervise expenditures of all county offices, departments, and institutions, including those departments in which the department head is an elected or appointed officer. (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,17,Calaveras_County.pdf,167
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,2.10.080 - Personnel administration.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.080 - Personnel administration.
The CEO is the county's personnel officer and may delegate related duties to one or more subordinates. He or she shall: A. Supervise and evaluate the performance of all county departments, within the limitations established by state law or the board of supervisors, by establishing standards, goals, and objectives for departmental performance and measuring performance against these standards, goals, and objectives. B. Assign projects to departments and review departmental expenditures to assure that they are necessary and proper. C. Employ assistants and/or utilize or coordinate the personnel of other County officers and utilize the services of outside expert facilities and services where appropriate. D. Appoint, transfer, discipline, and dismiss all non-elected department heads except as specifically required by law; such department heads shall serve at the pleasure of the CEO and the board of supervisors hereby delegates its authority to appoint, remove, and supervise such non-elected department heads to the CEO. For the positions for which the CEO is not the appointing authority under this chapter, unless otherwise stated in County Code, the CEO shall: (1) recommend to the board of supervisors the appointment of a qualified candidate to fill any vacancy occurring in that department head position and obtain the board's concurrence, and (2) recommend to the board of supervisors, for its consideration and determination, the transfer, discipline, or dismissal of such department head, when appropriate. E. Evaluate the on-the-job performance of each department head, except for elected department heads, at least once annually and prepare a written record of his or her review. (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,17,Calaveras_County.pdf,331
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,2.10.090 - Purchasing.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.090 - Purchasing.
The CEO is the county's purchasing agent, shall supervise and direct the administration of purchasing staff, and shall establish procedures for the efficient and cost-effective purchase of county supplies and goods, including fixed assets. (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,18,Calaveras_County.pdf,62
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,"2.10.100 - Other duties, responsibilities, and powers.","Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.100 - Other duties, responsibilities, and powers.
A. The CEO shall perform such investigations, studies, or surveys as the board of supervisors may request or as he/she deems necessary for the efficient use of manpower, material, facilities, and services. B. The CEO shall coordinate the planning, design and construction of physical facilities and assignment of space required for county services. He/she shall prepare, and keep current, a capital improvement plan, including recommended methods for financing, for adoption by the board of supervisors. C. The CEO shall recommend to the board of supervisors such organizational and staffing plans and proposals as, in his/her judgment, are necessary and desirable in order to efficiently provide county services. Such recommendations may include transfers, reassignments or consolidation of functions and services. D. The CEO shall represent the board of supervisors in matters relating to relationships with other governmental entities and enunciate and carry out the policies and views of the board. E. The CEO shall supervise and direct all central administrative services (e.g., information technology, building and grounds operations, etc.) as may be placed under his/her supervision by the board of supervisors. F. In cooperation with the county clerk, the CEO shall prepare the board agenda, evaluate departmental and other requests to determine if such requests should be submitted to the board, and make recommendations to the board on matters within his/her authority. G. The CEO shall supervise the performance of county departments, within the limitations established by state law or the board of supervisors, by coordinating the establishment of mutually acceptable standards, goals, and objectives for quality and quantity of departmental performance. H. The CEO shall have such additional powers and duties as established by resolution of the board of supervisors. I. This chapter shall not delegate to the CEO any duty otherwise delegated or imposed on any other County office or department by any federal or state statute or regulation. (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,18,Calaveras_County.pdf,389
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,2.10.110 - Limitations of chapter.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.110 - Limitations of chapter.
The board of supervisors intends to delegate to the CEO, to the maximum extent authorized by law, the authority to manage and coordinate the operations of the County's various departments, offices, and agencies. However, no provision of this chapter is intended to vest in the CEO the exercise of any duty specifically conferred by law on another officer of the County. (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,18,Calaveras_County.pdf,91
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER,2.10.120 - Severability.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.10 - COUNTY EXECUTIVE OFFICER | 2.10.120 - Severability.
If any section, sentence, clause, or phrase of the ordinance codified in this chapter is for any reason held to be unconstitutional or invalid, such decision shall not affect the validity of the remaining portion of this chapter. The board of supervisors declares that it would have passed this chapter and each section, subsection, sentence, clause, or phrase thereof, irrespective of the fact that any one or more sections, subsections, sentences, clauses, or phrases are declared unconstitutional or otherwise invalid. (Ord. No. 3184, § 1, 12-13-2022) ",Calaveras_County,18,Calaveras_County.pdf,119
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.12 - COUNTY SURVEYOR,,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.12 - COUNTY SURVEYOR | 
Sections: Footnotes: --- (5) --- State Law reference— For statutory provisions on county surveyors, see Gov. Code § 27550 et seq. ",Calaveras_County,19,Calaveras_County.pdf,34
