Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.36 - DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC WORKS,2.36.050 - O␀ce of road commissioner abolished.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.36 - DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC WORKS | 2.36.050 - O␀ce of road commissioner abolished.
The office of road commissioner is abolished and the duties of that office are transferred to the director of transportation. The director of transportation shall not be required to have any special permit, registration, or license. Any civil engineering functions which are required to be performed by the road commissioner shall be performed by a registered civil engineer acting under the authority of the director of transportation. (Ord. 2943 § 1(part), 2008). ",Calaveras_County,27,Calaveras_County.pdf,88
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.38 - PLANNING AGENCY,,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.38 - PLANNING AGENCY | 
Sections: ",Calaveras_County,27,Calaveras_County.pdf,3
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.38 - PLANNING AGENCY,2.38.010 - Purpose.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.38 - PLANNING AGENCY | 2.38.010 - Purpose.
The purpose of this chapter and Chapters 2.40 and 2.44 is to implement the requirements of the Planning Act, specifically Section 65100 of the Government Code. (Ord. 1216 § 1.00, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,27,Calaveras_County.pdf,53
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.38 - PLANNING AGENCY,2.38.020 - Creation—Membership.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.38 - PLANNING AGENCY | 2.38.020 - Creation—Membership.
There is created a planning agency which is composed of the following: A. County board of supervisors; B. County planning commission; C. County planning department. (Ord. 1216 § 1.02, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,28,Calaveras_County.pdf,49
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.38 - PLANNING AGENCY,2.38.030 - Function.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.38 - PLANNING AGENCY | 2.38.030 - Function.
The functions of the planning agency are as follows: A. It shall develop and maintain a general plan; B. It shall develop such specific plans as may be desirable or necessary; C. It shall periodically review the capital improvement program of the county; D. It shall perform such other functions as the board of supervisors may provide. (Ord. 1216 § 1.04, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,28,Calaveras_County.pdf,83
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.38 - PLANNING AGENCY,2.38.040 - Board of supervisors duties.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.38 - PLANNING AGENCY | 2.38.040 - Board of supervisors duties.
The board of supervisors, as a part of the Calaveras County planning agency, shall have such duties as are prescribed by state and local law. (Ord. 1216 § 4.00, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,28,Calaveras_County.pdf,47
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.40 - PLANNING DEPARTMENT,,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.40 - PLANNING DEPARTMENT | 
Sections: Footnotes: --- (12) --- State Law reference— For statutory provisions on planning departments, see Gov. Code §§ 65200 and 5201. ",Calaveras_County,28,Calaveras_County.pdf,35
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.40 - PLANNING DEPARTMENT,2.40.010 - Creation.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.40 - PLANNING DEPARTMENT | 2.40.010 - Creation.
Pursuant to the provisions of Government Code Section 65200, there is created a planning department of the county. (Ord. 1216 § 3.00, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,28,Calaveras_County.pdf,41
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.40 - PLANNING DEPARTMENT,2.40.020 - Duties.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.40 - PLANNING DEPARTMENT | 2.40.020 - Duties.
The planning department shall: A. Be responsible for the administration of the planning agency, for preparation of recommendations and decisions of the planning agency, and for maintaining records of the planning agency; B. Perform the duties required for the proper preparation and administration of the general plan as provided by state and local law; C. Perform the duties required for the proper preparation and administration of specific plans and regulations as provided by state and local law; D. Provide administrative support and professional advice to the planning commission and board of supervisors; E. Perform special studies and surveys as directed by the board of supervisors. (Ord. 1216 § 3.02, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,28,Calaveras_County.pdf,135
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.40 - PLANNING DEPARTMENT,2.40.030 - Planning director.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.40 - PLANNING DEPARTMENT | 2.40.030 - Planning director.
The county executive officer shall appoint a planning director, who shall be a person qualified by training, experience, and demonstrated ability to manage the affairs of the planning department. The planning director shall be the administrative officer of the planning department. (Ord. 1216 § 3.04, 1979). (Ord. No. 3197, § 1, 2-27-2024) ",Calaveras_County,29,Calaveras_County.pdf,84
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.40 - PLANNING DEPARTMENT,2.40.040 - Consultants.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.40 - PLANNING DEPARTMENT | 2.40.040 - Consultants.
The board may employ or contract with planning consultants and other specialists for such services as it requires to assist it in making land-use planning decisions. (Ord. 1216 § 3.06, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,29,Calaveras_County.pdf,45
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 
Sections: Footnotes: --- (13) --- State Law reference— For statutory provisions on planning commissions, see Gov. Code § 56150. ",Calaveras_County,29,Calaveras_County.pdf,31
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.010 - Creation.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.010 - Creation.
Pursuant to Government Code Section 65150, there is created a planning commission of the county. (Ord. 1216 § 2.00, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,29,Calaveras_County.pdf,38
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.020 - Members—Quali␀cations.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.020 - Members—Quali␀cations.
There shall be five members of the planning commission. The qualifications of the members shall be as follows: One member shall be registered to vote in supervisorial district 1; one member shall be registered to vote in supervisorial district 2; one member shall be registered to vote in supervisorial district 3; one member shall be registered to vote in supervisorial district 4; and one member shall be registered to vote in supervisorial district 5. (Ord. 1766 § 1, 1985: Ord. 1216 § 2.02, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,29,Calaveras_County.pdf,121
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.030 - Members—Ex o␀cio.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.030 - Members—Ex o␀cio.
The following are nonvoting ex officio members of the planning commission: A. Planning director; B. Public works director; C. County health officer; D. County counsel. (Ord. 1216 § 2.04, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,29,Calaveras_County.pdf,54
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.040 - Members—Selection—Term of o␀ce.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.040 - Members—Selection—Term of o␀ce.
Members of the planning commission shall be appointed by majority vote of the board of supervisors. A member from each supervisorial district shall be appointed to serve for a term which shall expire on the last day of December in each even year. (Ord. 2829 § 1, 2005: Ord. 2219 § 1, 1991: Ord. 1766 § 12, 1985: Ord. 1216 § 2.06, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,30,Calaveras_County.pdf,102
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.050 - Members—Extension of terms.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.050 - Members—Extension of terms.
By a majority vote, the board may extend the term of office of a member of the planning commission pending selection of his/her replacement. Such extension shall not exceed three months. (Ord. 1216 § 2.08, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,30,Calaveras_County.pdf,52
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.060 - Members—Removal.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.060 - Members—Removal.
Prior to the end of his/her term of office, a planning commission member may be removed from his/her seat upon majority vote of the board of supervisors. (Ord. 2342 § 1, 1993: Ord. 1636 § 1, 1984: Ord. 1216 § 2.10, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,30,Calaveras_County.pdf,74
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.080 - O␀cers.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.080 - O␀cers.
A. During its first regular meeting in February of each year, the planning commission shall by majority vote select a chairman and vice-chairman to serve through the last meeting of the succeeding January. Should the office of chairman or vice-chairman become vacant, the planning commission may by majority vote appoint a new officer to serve for the balance of the term. B. Prior to the end of his/her term of office, a planning commission officer may be removed by a majority vote of the members of the planning commission upon his/her conviction of a misdemeanor or felony, or his/her absence for three or more consecutive planning commission meetings. (Ord. 1216 § 2.14, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,30,Calaveras_County.pdf,141
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.090 - Duties.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.090 - Duties.
The planning commission shall hold public hearings and meetings and make decisions and recommendations on land use matters to the board of supervisors as required by state law and local ordinance, including, but not limited to, decisions on zoning, general plan amendments, reclamation plans, conditional use permits, variances, divisions of land, and subdivisions. (Ord. 1216 § 2.16, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,30,Calaveras_County.pdf,82
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.100 - Decisions and recommendations.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.100 - Decisions and recommendations.
A. Recommendations and decisions on zoning amendments, general plan amendments, reclamation plans, conditional use permits, variances, divisions of land and subdivisions shall be made by resolution. All other actions by the commission shall be by order of the commission. B. All planning commission orders and resolutions shall be written and shall show how each member voted thereon. (Ord. 1216 § 2.18, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,30,Calaveras_County.pdf,87
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.110 - Actions—Requisite vote.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.110 - Actions—Requisite vote.
Planning commission resolutions must be passed by at least three members voting ""aye"" thereon. Failure to receive three ""aye"" votes constitutes a denial. (Ord. 1766 § 3, 1985: Ord. 1216 § 2.20, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,31,Calaveras_County.pdf,60
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.120 - Rules of procedure.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.120 - Rules of procedure.
A. The planning commission may adopt rules of procedure to supplement the rules set forth in this chapter. B. Any such rules shall be consistent with this chapter, Chapters 2.38 and 2.40 and with state law. (Ord. 1216 § 2.22, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,31,Calaveras_County.pdf,64
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION,2.44.130 - Members—Compensation.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.44 - PLANNING COMMISSION | 2.44.130 - Members—Compensation.
Compensation of planning commission members shall be set by resolution of the board of supervisors. Compensation may include reasonable traveling expenses to and from the place of meetings held by the commission. (Ord. 1216 § 2.24, 1979). ",Calaveras_County,31,Calaveras_County.pdf,52
