Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.46 - ASSESSMENT APPEALS BOARD,2.46.010 - Creation.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.46 - ASSESSMENT APPEALS BOARD | 2.46.010 - Creation.
Pursuant to Section 16 of Article 13 of the Constitution of the State of California and Revenue and Taxation Code Section 1620 et seq., one separate assessment appeals board is created. (Ord. No. 2999, § 2, 9-27-2011) ",Calaveras_County,31,Calaveras_County.pdf,62
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.46 - ASSESSMENT APPEALS BOARD,2.46.020 - Membership and appointment.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.46 - ASSESSMENT APPEALS BOARD | 2.46.020 - Membership and appointment.
A. The assessment appeals board shall consist of five members appointed directly by the board of supervisors. The five members need not correspond to supervisorial districts. B. All assessment appeals hearings shall be before three of the appointed members and the conduct and conditions of hearings shall be governed by Revenue and Taxation Code Section 1620, et seq. (Ord. No. 2999, § 3, 9-27-2011) ",Calaveras_County,31,Calaveras_County.pdf,90
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.46 - ASSESSMENT APPEALS BOARD,2.46.030 - Pay and expenses.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.46 - ASSESSMENT APPEALS BOARD | 2.46.030 - Pay and expenses.
A. Each member of the assessment appeals board shall receive compensation for his or her services as set forth per a resolution adopted by the board of supervisors. B. Each member of the assessment appeals board shall be reimbursed for out-of-county expenses incurred in the discharge of his or her duties. (Ord. No. 2999, § 4, 9-27-2011) ",Calaveras_County,31,Calaveras_County.pdf,81
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.46 - ASSESSMENT APPEALS BOARD,2.46.040 - Legal advice.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.46 - ASSESSMENT APPEALS BOARD | 2.46.040 - Legal advice.
County counsel or a designated assistant or deputy shall provide legal advice to the assessment appeals board and recommend the use of outside counsel when necessary in connection with litigation matters. Counsel shall be present at assessment appeals hearings when findings of facts are requested by any applicant or when requested by the board. (Ord. No. 2999, § 5, 9-27-2011) ",Calaveras_County,32,Calaveras_County.pdf,78
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.46 - ASSESSMENT APPEALS BOARD,2.46.050 - Reserved.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.46 - ASSESSMENT APPEALS BOARD | 2.46.050 - Reserved.
