Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.48 - LIBRARY COMMISSION,2.48.030 - Organization.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.48 - LIBRARY COMMISSION | 2.48.030 - Organization.
A. The first meeting of the commission, after the appointment of all of the members thereof, shall be called by the county clerk, and at the time and place selected by the county clerk the commission shall organize itself. B. At the first meeting the commission shall elect one of its members as chairman, elect a secretary, and provide for the time and place of holding meetings and the manner in which special meetings shall be called. The commission may establish rules for the proceedings of the commission. (Ord. 254 §§ 3, 4, 1961). ",Calaveras_County,32,Calaveras_County.pdf,115
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.48 - LIBRARY COMMISSION,2.48.040 - Term.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.48 - LIBRARY COMMISSION | 2.48.040 - Term.
Each member of the commission shall continue to act and to be a member of the same at the pleasure of the board of supervisors, or for such term as might hereafter be prescribed by the board of supervisors by its order or resolution. (Ord. 254 § 5, 1961). ",Calaveras_County,33,Calaveras_County.pdf,61
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.48 - LIBRARY COMMISSION,2.48.050 - Duties.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.48 - LIBRARY COMMISSION | 2.48.050 - Duties.
The commission shall act in an advisory capacity to the board of supervisors in all matters pertaining to library service furnished by the county free library. The commission shall familiarize itself with all phases of the operation of the library and shall make recommendations to the board of supervisors for the improvement, future development and maintenance of the county free library service. (Ord. 254 § 6, 1961). ",Calaveras_County,33,Calaveras_County.pdf,80
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.48 - LIBRARY COMMISSION,2.48.060 - Compensation and expenses.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.48 - LIBRARY COMMISSION | 2.48.060 - Compensation and expenses.
The members of the commission shall serve as such without compensation, but each member of the commission shall be allowed his necessary traveling expenses in going to and from the place of meetings of the commission and his regular place of residence. (Ord. 254 § 7, 1961). ",Calaveras_County,33,Calaveras_County.pdf,58
