Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.52 - FISH AND GAME COMMISSION,2.52.020 - Membership.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.52 - FISH AND GAME COMMISSION | 2.52.020 - Membership.
The commission shall consist of seven members, all of whom shall be registered electors, residing within the county, who shall be appointed by the board of supervisors. One commission member shall be appointed from each supervisorial district within the county and two commission members shall be appointed as members at large from any supervisorial district within the county. In the event a supervisorial district vacancy lasts more than ninety (90) days, the board of supervisors may fill the vacancy through the appointment of another member-at-large from the County of Calaveras until such a time as the position is filled by a qualified candidate from the relevant supervisorial district. (Ord. No. 3025, § 3, 12-10-2013; Ord. No. 3203, § 3, 5-28-2024) ",Calaveras_County,33,Calaveras_County.pdf,168
