Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.52 - FISH AND GAME COMMISSION,2.52.040 - Term.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.52 - FISH AND GAME COMMISSION | 2.52.040 - Term.
Each member of the commission shall continue to act and to be a member of the commission at the pleasure of the board of supervisors, or for such term as might hereafter be prescribed by the board of supervisors. (Ord. No. 3025, § 3, 12-10-2013; Ord. No. 3203, § 3, 5-28-2024) ",Calaveras_County,34,Calaveras_County.pdf,84
Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL,Chapter 2.52 - FISH AND GAME COMMISSION,2.52.050 - Powers and duties.,"Calaveras_County | Title 2 - ADMINISTRATION AND PERSONNEL | Chapter 2.52 - FISH AND GAME COMMISSION | 2.52.050 - Powers and duties.
The fish and game commission shall have the following powers and duties: A. To advise the board of supervisors on all matters affecting the conservation, propagation, preservation, and management of fish and wildlife that is within the jurisdiction of the board of supervisors; B. To coordinate efforts in habitat improvement, public awareness, and resource education within Calaveras County, to provide the citizens of Calaveras County with a forum to express their concerns, opinions, beliefs, and views pertaining to the conservation, propagation, preservation, and management of fish and wildlife in Calaveras County, and to perform such other duties and functions as the board of supervisors may direct; C. To make recommendations to the board of supervisors regarding the budget for use of the fish and wildlife propagation fund of the county in accordance with the provisions of Chapter 2 (commencing with Section 13100) of Division 10 of the Fish and Game Code, To expend, grant and otherwise provide for the use of the funds as allowed by Fish and Game Code Section 13103 within the budget approved by the board of supervisors and in compliance with Chapter 3.28 herein, the County's purchasing system; Chapter 3.29, Bidding Procedures for Public Projects, when applicable; and D. To adopt bylaws and operating procedures to govern the Commission in the execution of its duties; E. In carrying out the duties set forth in this section, the commission shall comply with all ordinances, resolutions, rules, and regulations established by the board of supervisors concerning all matters within the commission's authority, including but not limited to: contracts, the expenditures of funds, and meetings; F. The commission is subject to the requirements of Government Code section 54950. et seq., also known as the Ralph M. Brown Act. G. Members of the commission must comply with all applicable provisions of the Political Reform Act, Government Code section 81000 et seq., including but not limited to the filing of conflict of interest forms, and the training required by Assembly Bill 1234. (Ord. No. 3025, § 3, 12-10-2013; Ord. No. 3203, § 3, 5-28-2024) ",Calaveras_County,34,Calaveras_County.pdf,452
