A. All equipment with a useful life of one year or longer, which either has a minimum value of five thousand dollars or holds title/registration with the California Department of Motor Vehicles regardless of value, shall be carried on a department's inventory unless otherwise authorized by the administrative coordinator. B. All structures and improvements with an initial value of twenty-five thousand dollars shall be carried on a department's inventory unless otherwise authorized by the administrative coordinator. C. Infrastructure with an initial value of one hundred thousand dollars or greater shall be carried on a department's inventory unless otherwise authorized by the administrative coordinator. D. Capital projects that exceed fifty thousand dollars shall be accounted for in the capital outlay fund, except for proprietary funds and the road fund. (Ord. No. 3112, § 1, 2-12-2019) Editor's note— Ord. No. 3112, § 1, adopted February 12, 2019, repealed the former § 2.60.005, and enacted a new § 2.60.005 as set out herein. The former § 2.60.005 pertained to similar subject matter and derived from Ord. No. 1844, 1986; Ord. No. 2431, 1995; Ord. No. 2615, 2000 and Ord. No. 2888, 2006. ",Calaveras_County,36,Calaveras_County.pdf,286
