Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.32 - CALAMITY,3.32.010 - Purpose.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.32 - CALAMITY | 3.32.010 - Purpose.
The purpose of this chapter is to implement the provisions of Revenue and Taxation Code Section 170, and does not limit, modify or extend the provisions contained therein. (Ord. 2778 (part), 2004: Ord. 1207 § 1, 1979: Ord. 1034 § 1, 1978). ",Calaveras_County,109,Calaveras_County.pdf,73
Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.32 - CALAMITY,3.32.015 - Applicable events.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.32 - CALAMITY | 3.32.015 - Applicable events.
To be eligible for reassessment, the damage or destruction to the property must be caused by an unforeseeable occurrence beyond the control of the property owner. It includes a diminution in the value of the property whether or not the governor has proclaimed that the property is in an area in a state of disaster. Property includes possessory interests where the misfortune or calamity has caused the permit or other right to be suspended or restricted. (Ord. 2778 (part), 2004). ",Calaveras_County,109,Calaveras_County.pdf,101
Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.32 - CALAMITY,3.32.020 - Application by owner.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.32 - CALAMITY | 3.32.020 - Application by owner.
Any assessee of taxable property, or any person liable for taxes thereon, may apply for reassessment if that property was damaged or destroyed by a misfortune or calamity. The application must be filed within twelve months of the misfortune or calamity on a form prescribed by the assessor. (Ord. 2778 (part), 2004: Ord. 1207 § 2, 1979: Ord. 1034 § 2, 1978). ",Calaveras_County,109,Calaveras_County.pdf,100
Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.32 - CALAMITY,3.32.030 - Assessor's duty.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.32 - CALAMITY | 3.32.030 - Assessor's duty.
The assessor may initiate reassessment where the assessor determines that taxable property was damaged or destroyed by misfortune or calamity within the preceding twelve months. (Ord. 2778 (part), 2004: Ord. 2451 § 1, 1995: Ord. 1207 § 3, 1979: Ord. 1034 § 3, 1978). ",Calaveras_County,110,Calaveras_County.pdf,84
Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.34 - ASSESSMENT OF GRAPEVINES REPLACED AS THE RESULT OF PHYLLOXERA INFESTATION OR PIERCE'S DISEASE,,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.34 - ASSESSMENT OF GRAPEVINES REPLACED AS THE RESULT OF PHYLLOXERA INFESTATION OR PIERCE'S DISEASE | 
Sections: ",Calaveras_County,110,Calaveras_County.pdf,3
Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.34 - ASSESSMENT OF GRAPEVINES REPLACED AS THE RESULT OF PHYLLOXERA INFESTATION OR PIERCE'S DISEASE,3.34.010 - Assessment of replacement vines—Phylloxera or Pierce's Disease.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.34 - ASSESSMENT OF GRAPEVINES REPLACED AS THE RESULT OF PHYLLOXERA INFESTATION OR PIERCE'S DISEASE | 3.34.010 - Assessment of replacement vines—Phylloxera or Pierce's Disease.
When grapevines that are less than fifteen years old are removed solely as a result of phylloxera infestation or Pierce's Disease, and when substantially equivalent grapevines are planted on the same parcel as the removed grapevines, the initial base year value for the replacement grapevines shall be the base year values of the removed grapevines factored to the lien date of the first taxable year of the replacement vines. (Ord. 2654 § 2(part), 2001). ",Calaveras_County,110,Calaveras_County.pdf,104
Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.34 - ASSESSMENT OF GRAPEVINES REPLACED AS THE RESULT OF PHYLLOXERA INFESTATION OR PIERCE'S DISEASE,3.34.020 - Substantially equivalent grapevines—Meaning.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.34 - ASSESSMENT OF GRAPEVINES REPLACED AS THE RESULT OF PHYLLOXERA INFESTATION OR PIERCE'S DISEASE | 3.34.020 - Substantially equivalent grapevines—Meaning.
For the purposes of this chapter, replacement grapevines are substantially equivalent to removed grapevines if the replacement grapevines are a type similar to, and are planted at a density similar to, the removed grapevines. (Ord. 2654 § 2(part), 2001). ",Calaveras_County,110,Calaveras_County.pdf,62
Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.34 - ASSESSMENT OF GRAPEVINES REPLACED AS THE RESULT OF PHYLLOXERA INFESTATION OR PIERCE'S DISEASE,3.34.030 - Certi␀cation by agricultural commissioner.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.34 - ASSESSMENT OF GRAPEVINES REPLACED AS THE RESULT OF PHYLLOXERA INFESTATION OR PIERCE'S DISEASE | 3.34.030 - Certi␀cation by agricultural commissioner.
The assessment authorized by this chapter shall apply only if the county agricultural commissioner certifies in writing that phylloxera infestation or Pierce's Disease is the sole cause necessitating removal of the existing grapevines. (Ord. 2654 § 2(part), 2001). ",Calaveras_County,110,Calaveras_County.pdf,59
