Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.54 - CHARGES REASONABLY NECESSARY TO RECOVER COSTS OF PROVIDING COPIES UNDER THE PUBLIC RECORDS ACT,3.54.010 - Purpose.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.54 - CHARGES REASONABLY NECESSARY TO RECOVER COSTS OF PROVIDING COPIES UNDER THE PUBLIC RECORDS ACT | 3.54.010 - Purpose.
This chapter is adopted to authorize county departments to recover costs associated with providing copies of public records beyond direct costs of duplication as authorized by California Government Code Section 54985. (Ord. 2909 § 1(part), 2007). ",Calaveras_County,120,Calaveras_County.pdf,50
Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.54 - CHARGES REASONABLY NECESSARY TO RECOVER COSTS OF PROVIDING COPIES UNDER THE PUBLIC RECORDS ACT,3.54.020 - Weighted salary as a recoverable cost.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.54 - CHARGES REASONABLY NECESSARY TO RECOVER COSTS OF PROVIDING COPIES UNDER THE PUBLIC RECORDS ACT | 3.54.020 - Weighted salary as a recoverable cost.
The weighted hourly salary of a county custodian of records, or his or her designee, for actual time spent in complying with a Public Records Act request is a cost beyond the cost of direct duplication and is recoverable under Govt. Code Section 54985. (Ord. 2909 § 1(part), 2007). ",Calaveras_County,120,Calaveras_County.pdf,70
Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.54 - CHARGES REASONABLY NECESSARY TO RECOVER COSTS OF PROVIDING COPIES UNDER THE PUBLIC RECORDS ACT,3.54.030 - Weighted salary of custodian of records shall be charged.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.54 - CHARGES REASONABLY NECESSARY TO RECOVER COSTS OF PROVIDING COPIES UNDER THE PUBLIC RECORDS ACT | 3.54.030 - Weighted salary of custodian of records shall be charged.
In addition to the direct cost of providing documents requested under the Public Records Act, the board of supervisors authorizes each department head and his or her custodians of records and/or designees to charge parties requesting public records a sum reasonably necessary to recover such additional costs of furnishing copies as permitted by law. Such additional costs shall not exceed the weighted hourly salary of the custodian or his designee actually performing search, compilation, delivery, and necessary redaction of the requested documents. (Ord. 2909 § 1(part), 2007). ",Calaveras_County,120,Calaveras_County.pdf,113
