Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.55 - ADVERTISING ON CALAVERAS TRANSIT VEHICLES AND SHELTERS,3.55.010 - Introduction.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.55 - ADVERTISING ON CALAVERAS TRANSIT VEHICLES AND SHELTERS | 3.55.010 - Introduction.
A. As Calaveras County is the operator of the county's public transit system, the county board of supervisors is responsible for determining Calaveras Transit policies. The purpose of this chapter is to establish guidelines for interior and exterior advertising on Calaveras Transit vehicles and shelters. The board intends its vehicles and bus shelters are subject to the viewpoint-neutral restrictions set forth below. B. The county has approved the practice of commercial advertising on the exterior and interior of its vehicles, as well as on bus shelters, as a means of raising revenue for the transit system. Revenue generated from advertising is returned to the transit operating budget and used to reduce local contributions to fund operations. C. Calaveras Transit may use exterior and interior vehicle advertising itself to promote public awareness of transit programs and services. D. The ordinance codified in this chapter repeals and supersedes Resolution No. 20150113001, except that the fee schedule approved by Resolution No. 20150113001 shall remain in effect until changed by the board of supervisors. E. The board of supervisors designates the director of public works to implement the provisions of this chapter. (Ord. No. 3056, § I, 7-14-2015) ",Calaveras_County,121,Calaveras_County.pdf,251
Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.55 - ADVERTISING ON CALAVERAS TRANSIT VEHICLES AND SHELTERS,3.55.020 - Commercial advertising standards.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.55 - ADVERTISING ON CALAVERAS TRANSIT VEHICLES AND SHELTERS | 3.55.020 - Commercial advertising standards.
A. In order to realize the maximum benefit from the sale of advertising space, the program will be managed in a manner that produces as much revenue as practical, while ensuring that advertising does not: 1. Discourage the use of the transit system. 2. Diminish Calaveras Transit's reputation in the community. 3. In any way interfere with operations or jeopardize the safety of passengers, employees, and the public. 4. Cause offense to its customers or the general public. B. Calaveras Transit provides opportunities for interior and exterior advertising subject to the following guidelines: 1. Acceptance of all advertising on Calaveras Transit vehicles is subject to the county's approval. The county reserves the right at any time to alter, cancel, or reject any advertisement including, but not limited to that which in its sole judgment is not in keeping with the best interests of the county. 2. Permitted advertisements shall mean and refer to only commercial advertisements, which propose a commercial trans Because Calaveras Transit serves persons of all ages and backgrounds and strives to create a comfortable and enjoyab experience for all passengers, permitted advertisements shall not include any of the following: a. Political advertising, including, but not limited to, advertisement implying a position for or against any political candidate, public issue, or subject. b. Advertisements that display any word, phrase, symbol, or character likely to interfere with, mislead, or distract traffic, or conflict with any traffic control device. c. Advertisements that incorporate any rotating, revolving, or flashing devices, or any other moving or otherwise distracting parts. d. Advertisements that contain false, misleading, or deceptive images. e. Advertisements that promote illegal goods, services, or activities, or which advocate violence or crime. f. Advertisements that contain an image or description of violence. g. Advertisements that directly or indirectly promote the sale or use of a firearm or contain an image or depiction of a firearm. h. Advertisements that contain or promote the sale or use of alcohol, tobacco products, or electronic cigarettes. i. Advertisements for adult products, services, or entertainment directed to sexual stimulation. j. Advertisements that contain sexually explicit material. k. Advertising of contraceptive products or hygiene products of an intimately personal nature. l. Advertising that contains discriminatory, derogatory, negative or personal attacks against individuals, groups, or organizations. m. Advertisements that infringe upon any copyright, trademark or registered mark. n. Advertisements implying a position for or against any religion. o. Advertisements that contain images, copy or concepts that actively denigrate a specific age, religion, ethnic or gender group. p. Advertisements that contain images, copy or concepts that actively denigrate public transportation. q. Advertisements that imply or declare an endorsement by Calaveras County of any service, product, or point of view, without prior written authorization of the county public works director, or his designee. r. Other noncommercial advertisements or noncommercial speech. s. Advertisements or any material contained in it, that direct viewers to a website or telephone number that contains material that violates this policy. t. Exceptions to the above restrictions include governmental entities, or public entities specifically created by government action, which may acquire advertising space for messages that advance specific government purposes, except the space may not be used for advertising for or against a political candidate or issue of public debate. (Ord. No. 3056, § I, 7-14-2015) ",Calaveras_County,121,Calaveras_County.pdf,732
Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE,Chapter 3.55 - ADVERTISING ON CALAVERAS TRANSIT VEHICLES AND SHELTERS,3.55.030 - Production and placement guidelines.,"Calaveras_County | Title 3 - REVENUE AND FINANCE | Chapter 3.55 - ADVERTISING ON CALAVERAS TRANSIT VEHICLES AND SHELTERS | 3.55.030 - Production and placement guidelines.
A. Advertiser shall pay one hundred percent of the printing and installation costs for its advertisement. Advertiser shall provide, in the event of vandalism or collision, at no cost to the county, all materials, and labor necessary to repair or replace the graphics. All graphics are to be installed on Calaveras Transit buses during regular business hours at the transit yard located as specified by the county public works director, or his designee. B. Advertisers shall comply with the bus advertising agreement guidelines included in the bus advertising space agreement. (Ord. No. 3056, § I, 7-14-2015) ",Calaveras_County,122,Calaveras_County.pdf,129
