This chapter shall take effect immediately upon its approval by a majority of voters at the November 3, 2020, statewide general election and become operative on January 1, 2021. Any cannabis that is cultivated pursuant to Chapter 17.95 of this code between January 1, 2020 and December 31, 2020, and harvested between said dates, prior to the operative date of this chapter on January 1, 2021, shall be deemed product realized in the year 2020 for purposes of cannabis cultivation taxation whether or not said product is actually processed in the year 2020 and entered into the state's track and trace system provided in Business and Professions Code Section 26067, et seq., within the year of 2020. Solely for the purpose of taxing cannabis cultivation taking place in the calendar year of 2020, and applying strictly thereto, former Section 3.56.030(B)(1), (2) of the county code (as ordained by Ordinance No. 3071) shall survive the replacement of former Chapter 3.56 by this chapter; the terms ""licensees or registrants"" in former Section 3.56.030(B)(1), (2) shall mean and refer to a county permit for cultivation under Chapter 17.95. The administrative provisions and procedures of this chapter shall apply to the administration and enforcement of taxation under this section, including as to any deficiency determinations, investigations, and appeals of taxes under this section. (Measure G, § 1, 11-3-2020) ",Calaveras_County,133,Calaveras_County.pdf,328
