The board of supervisors finds that it is necessary to establish appropriate procedures for the administrative and summary abatement of public nuisances and code violations. The procedures established in these sections are in addition to any other legal remedy, criminal or civil, permitted by law which may be pursued to address these violations of code or other applicable laws. Unless expressly stated otherwise, the abatement provisions of this chapter shall govern all other nuisance abatement procedures established in any chapter of the county code. (Ord. No. 3081, § 3, 2-28-2017) ",Calaveras_County,221,Calaveras_County.pdf,116
