A. The written permits required by this chapter shall be issued by the road commissioner for any lawful use, subject to conditions set forth in the chapter and required by law. B. The road commissioner shall prescribe and provide a regular form of application for a permit required by this chapter. The application form shall contain space for the applicant's name, address, and contractor's name, license number and primary place of business, if the applicant proposes to employ a contractor, together with such detail as in the judgement of the road commissioner is necessary to establish the purpose and use, the location, dimensions, estimated date of commencement and completion of encroachment. The application form shall be completed and signed by the applicant and filed with the director. (Ord. 280 § 20, 1963). ",Calaveras_County,374,Calaveras_County.pdf,160
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.08 - ENCROACHMENT ON PUBLIC HIGHWAYS,12.08.110 - Permit application—Attached exhibits.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.08 - ENCROACHMENT ON PUBLIC HIGHWAYS | 12.08.110 - Permit application—Attached exhibits.
