The applicant shall also enclose with, attach to or add to the application copies of the written order or consent to any work thereunder, required by law, the public utilities commission, sanitary districts, water districts or any other public body having jurisdiction. A permit shall not be issued until and unless such order or consent, if required, is first obtained and evidence thereof filed with the road commissioner. The permittee shall keep himself adequately informed of all state and federal laws and local ordinances and regulations which in any manner affect the permit. The applicant shall at all times comply with and shall cause all his agents and employees to comply with all such laws, ordinances, regulations, decisions, court and similar authoritative orders; and shall protect and indemnify the county and all of its officers, agents and employees against any claims of liability proximately caused by the violation of any such law, ordinance, regulations or order issued under police power and in accordance with law, whether by himself or by his agents or employees. (Ord. 280 § 22, 1963). ",Calaveras_County,374,Calaveras_County.pdf,213
