A. Any person, firm, corporation or other body or association of persons who violates this chapter is guilty of a misdemeanor and is punishable by a fine of not more than five hundred dollars, or by imprisonment in the county jail for a period of not more than one hundred eighty days, or by both. B. Each day's violation of this chapter is a separate offense. (Ord. 280 § 64, 1963). ",Calaveras_County,380,Calaveras_County.pdf,89
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.09 - OUTDOOR DINING ENCROACHMENT PERMITS,,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.09 - OUTDOOR DINING ENCROACHMENT PERMITS | 
