The definitions in this section shall govern the contents of this chapter and of park rules which are published under its authority. The definition of a word applies to any of its variants. A. ""Aquaplane"" means a device including but not limited to water skis which may be used for carrying one or more persons or property while being towed behind or propelled by a boat. B. ""Boat"" means a device in or upon which one or more persons or property may be carried over, on or beneath the surface other than an aquaplane. C. ""Park manager"" means the operator, manager, owner, lessee or governmental representative controlling and supervising the recreation area. D. ""Public waters"" means a lake, river, stream or other body of water, whether natural or artificial, situated within or partially within the county and over which the county has police power jurisdiction, either exclusively or concurrently with the United States, the state or some other county or combination thereof. E. ""Recreation area"" means park or recreation area situated within the unincorporated area of the county, operated, owned, leased or controlled by an individual, partnership, corporation or governmental agency. (Ord. 391 §§ 200-206, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,394,Calaveras_County.pdf,257
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.030 - Inclusion of chapter provisions in park rules.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.030 - Inclusion of chapter provisions in park rules.
The park manager may invoke any or all provisions of this chapter, and if they are so invoked they will have the same force as if they were included in this section, by submitting his proposed park rules containing the appropriate provisions of this chapter to the sheriff for concurrence and the board of supervisors for approval. This approval, if granted, will be in the form of a resolution of the board ordering the inclusion of appropriate parts of the park rules within the scope of this chapter. Such park rules must contain a description and map of the territory for which approval is requested. Such park rules must be posted at the entrance or entrance gate of the recreation area and at bulletin boards or other prominent places of public notice within the recreation area. (Ord. 391 § 101, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,394,Calaveras_County.pdf,159
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.040 - Entry restriction.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.040 - Entry restriction.
It is unlawful for any person to enter a recreation area or open one thereof except as permitted by the park manager. (Ord. 391 § 300, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,395,Calaveras_County.pdf,37
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.050 - Designation of open and closed areas—Authorized.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.050 - Designation of open and closed areas—Authorized.
By rules adopted from time to time a park manager may establish and designate open and closed areas within the recreation area. (Ord. 391 § 301, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,395,Calaveras_County.pdf,37
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.060 - Designation of open and closed areas—Standards.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.060 - Designation of open and closed areas—Standards.
Standards for the designation of open and closed areas are as follows: A. The park manager shall designate the following portions of the recreation area as closed areas: 1. Areas unsafe for use by the public; 2. Areas subject to unreasonable fire hazards; 3. Areas without adequate sanitary facilities; and 4. Areas requiring special protection for the benefit of wildlife and planted or natural vegetation. B. The park manager shall designate all portions of the recreation area not designated as closed as open areas. (Ord. 391 § 302, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,395,Calaveras_County.pdf,116
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.070 - Designation of open and closed areas—Posting of closed areas.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.070 - Designation of open and closed areas—Posting of closed areas.
Portions of the recreation area designated as closed areas pursuant to this chapter shall be posted along the exterior boundaries of such portion of the recreation area by appropriate signs. (Ord. 391 § 303, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,395,Calaveras_County.pdf,46
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.080 - Aircraft and parachutes restricted.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.080 - Aircraft and parachutes restricted.
No person shall land any aircraft on or take off in any aircraft on public waters, or parachute any person or object into the recreation area, except with the approval of the park manager. (Ord. 1524 § 1, 1982: Ord. 391 § 304, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,395,Calaveras_County.pdf,64
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.090 - Pedestrian access.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.090 - Pedestrian access.
Pedestrian access into the recreation area shall be permitted only at points established by the park manager. No person shall climb over or otherwise pass over or under any perimeter fence of the recreation area. (Ord. 391 § 305, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,395,Calaveras_County.pdf,53
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.100 - Fences and gates.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.100 - Fences and gates.
No person shall cut, mutilate or in any way damage or alter any fence around the recreation area. No person shall open closed gates nor close open gates around the recreation area without the express written permission of the park manager. (Ord. 391 § 306, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,395,Calaveras_County.pdf,59
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.110 - Vehicular access.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.110 - Vehicular access.
Entrance by motor vehicle, bicycle or other wheeled conveyance, whether powered or not shall be only upon roads designated by the park manager. No person shall operate a motor vehicle, bicycle or other wheeled conveyance, whether powered or not, within any recreational areas except upon areas provided therefor and as provided in this chapter. (Ord. 391 § 307, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,396,Calaveras_County.pdf,81
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.120 - Operation of motor vehicles.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.120 - Operation of motor vehicles.
It is unlawful to operate any motor vehicle which is not currently licensed except where designated by appropriate signs. It is unlawful to operate a motor vehicle if the operator does not have a current operator's permit except where designated by appropriate signs. (Ord. 628 Art. II (part), 1971: Ord. 391 § 308, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,396,Calaveras_County.pdf,74
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.130 - Destruction or alteration of recreation.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.130 - Destruction or alteration of recreation.
It is unlawful to pick, dig, cut, mark, mutilate, injure, destroy, alter, move, burn or carry away any plant, tree, sign or structure, natural feature or improvement, or any part thereof, post any bill or otherwise make any change in the recreation area except with the express written permission of the park manager. (Ord. 391 § 400, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,396,Calaveras_County.pdf,84
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.140 - Disposal of waste and litter.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.140 - Disposal of waste and litter.
It is unlawful to leave any waste material, object or litter of any kind, except in receptacles specifically designated for the disposal of such waste materials, objects or litters. (Ord. 391 § 401, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,396,Calaveras_County.pdf,49
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.150 - Fire—Open.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.150 - Fire—Open.
It is unlawful to light, build or maintain an open fire except when permitted by posted order of the park manager and within designated and posted camping areas and picnic areas. (Ord. 391 § 402, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,396,Calaveras_County.pdf,47
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.160 - Fire—In containers.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.160 - Fire—In containers.
It is unlawful to light, build or maintain other fires except in fireplaces constructed by the park manager and in portable camp stoves or charcoal grills designed for the purpose of securely containing fire, and in proper condition and repair so as to contain fire. (Ord. 391 § 403, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,396,Calaveras_County.pdf,65
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.170 - Hunting.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.170 - Hunting.
It is unlawful to molest, injure or kill any bird or animal Of any kind, or to disturb the natural or artificial habitat of any bird or animal of any kind, except in areas and in times designated as hunting areas and seasons for specific prey, and under and pursuant to rules adopted by the park manager and the applicable hunting laws of the state. (Ord. 391 § 404, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,396,Calaveras_County.pdf,85
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.180 - Motor vehicle speed limit.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.180 - Motor vehicle speed limit.
It is unlawful to operate a motor vehicle of any kind at a speed in excess of twenty-five miles per hour, except where a higher or lower speed is permitted or required by a rule adopted by the park manager and such higher or lower speed limit has been posted by signs displayed at the commencement and end of such a higher or lower speed zone and at intervals of not more than one-half mile along the distance of such a higher or lower speed zone. (Ord. 391 § 405, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,397,Calaveras_County.pdf,104
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.190 - Operation or parking of vehicles o␀ the road.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.190 - Operation or parking of vehicles o␀ the road.
It is unlawful to operate, drive or park a land motor vehicle, or land vehicle of any kind, except in the paved or otherwise improved surfaces of roads and designated parking lots. It is unlawful to park a motor vehicle on any paved area of the park which has been closed to the public by means of locked gates or by posting signs. (Ord. 1601 § 1, 1983: Ord. 391 § 406, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,397,Calaveras_County.pdf,95
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.200 - Mu␀er required on internal combustion engine—Exception.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.200 - Mu␀er required on internal combustion engine—Exception.
It is unlawful to operate an internal combustion engine of any kind without an efficient, operative muffler, except in areas and at times designated for such purpose by the park manager by an adoption of an appropriate rule or rules. (Ord. 391 § 407, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,397,Calaveras_County.pdf,58
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.210 - Firearms—Possession.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.210 - Firearms—Possession.
It is unlawful to carry or possess a firearm, gas-operated gun, bow and arrow, or other instrument capable of firing a projectile, except when in possession of a written permit permitting such carrying or possession issued by the park manager pursuant to rules adopted by him. (Ord. 391 § 408, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,397,Calaveras_County.pdf,67
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.220 - Firearms—Discharge.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.220 - Firearms—Discharge.
It is unlawful to discharge or otherwise use a firearm, gas-operated gun, bow and arrow, or other instrument capable of firing a projectile, except when in the possession of the permit mentioned in Section 12.20.210 and when engaged in hunting permitted by Section 12.20.170, or when at a range established for the use of firearms, gas-operated guns, bows and arrows, or other instruments capable of firing a projectile. (Ord. 391 § 409, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,397,Calaveras_County.pdf,105
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.230 - Fireworks and explosives.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.230 - Fireworks and explosives.
It is unlawful to possess or discharge fireworks, including but not limited to, safe and sane fireworks, or explosive material of any kind, except by written permit issued by the park manager, and in accordance with applicable state laws and other applicable ordinances of the county, which are more restrictive than this chapter. (Ord. 391 § 410, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,397,Calaveras_County.pdf,74
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.240 - Dogs and other domestic animals—Exemption.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.240 - Dogs and other domestic animals—Exemption.
A. It is unlawful to have a dog or other domestic animal in a swimming area, upon a beach, or where food is served, or in a designated and posted camping area between the hours of eight p.m. and seven a.m. B. It is also unlawful to have any dog or other domestic animal in the park except on leash not longer than six feet, and attended at all times, except livestock on recreational land pursuant to a grazing lease made by the park manager. C. The prohibitions found in subsections A and B of this section shall apply to all recreation areas in the county unless specifically exempted or allowed pursuant to rules adopted by the park manager. (Ord. 1897 § 1, 1987; Ord. 628 Art. II (part), 1971; Ord. 394 §§ 1, 2, 1967; Ord. 391 § 411, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,398,Calaveras_County.pdf,192
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.250 - Horses and other beasts of burden.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.250 - Horses and other beasts of burden.
It is unlawful to ride horses or other beasts of burden except in areas and on roads and trails designated by rule adopted by the park manager and posted or marked for that purpose. (Ord. 391 § 412, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,398,Calaveras_County.pdf,49
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.260 - Swimming—Area restricted.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.260 - Swimming—Area restricted.
A. Swimming, bathing, wading and diving are permitted only along a shoreline within open areas of the recreational area, and elsewhere two hundred feet or more from the nearest shoreline. B. It is unlawful to swim, bathe, wade or dive in any portion of the lake except as provided in this section. (Ord. 391 § 500, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,398,Calaveras_County.pdf,78
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.270 - Swimming—Exclusive areas.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.270 - Swimming—Exclusive areas.
A. Areas designated and posted as exclusive swimming beaches and areas of the lake buoyed as exclusive swimming areas, shall be used only for the purpose of swimming, bathing, wading and diving. B. It is unlawful to use a beach designated and posted as an exclusive swimming beach, and an area of the lake buoyed as an exclusive swimming area, for purposes of boating, aquaplaning, fishing or similar activities. (Ord. 391 § 501, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,398,Calaveras_County.pdf,101
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.280 - Fishing.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.280 - Fishing.
A. Shore fishing and fishing while wading is permitted along any shoreline within open areas of the park, except in exclusive swimming areas designated and posted pursuant to Section 12.20.270 and except where posted ""No Fishing"" pursuant to rules adopted by the park manager. Fishing from boats is permitted everywhere except where posted ""No Fishing"" pursuant to a rule adopted by the park manager and except in marked channels of a body of water. B. It is unlawful to fish in any portion of a lake except as provided in this section and as permitted by applicable state law to the extent that state law is more restrictive than this chapter. (Ord. 391 § 502, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,398,Calaveras_County.pdf,141
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.290 - Boating.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.290 - Boating.
It is unlawful to do any of the following: A. Boat Sewage. To discharge or dump into the lake any waste of any kind, or to place on the lake any boat containing marine sanitation devices which are not in conformity with federal or state laws, regulations or rules; B. Launching. To launch a boat at other than sites designated and posted for launching, pursuant to rules adopted by the park manager; C. Landing. To land, moor or dock a boat at sites designated, posted and restricted for other uses; D. 1. Night Operation of Boats. It is prohibited to operate a boat between one hour after sunset and one hour before sunrise unless specifically allowed pursuant to rules adopted by the park manager, 2. On all other recreational lakes in Calaveras County, it shall be the decision of the park manager whether or not to allow night boating. Such managers may allow night boating without the requirement of a written permit; E. Commercial Operation. To offer to operate any boat for hire, or to take passengers upon a boat for a fee, without a written permit, issued by the park manager, or a contract or concession agreement with the park manager. To operate a boat for hire, including rental units without having the maximum passenger carrying capacity (the number of persons authorized by state or local law and/or, in the absence thereof, by ratings figured on outboard boating club manufacturer's ratings) plainly posted in a conspicuous place inside the watercraft; F. Restricted Speed Zones. To operate any boat at more than the restricted speed when in a restricted speed zone. Restricted speed zones shall be established by the park manager by the adoption of rules and all such restricted speed zones shall be posted at reasonable intervals. Restricted speed zones established by this subsection are in addition to general speed limits established by state law. (Ord. 1897 § 2, 1987; Ord. 1685 § 2, 1984; Ord. 1649 § 1, 1984; Ord. 628 Art. II (part), 1971; Ord. 391 § 503, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,399,Calaveras_County.pdf,439
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.300 - Aquaplaning—Prohibited in certain areas.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.300 - Aquaplaning—Prohibited in certain areas.
It is unlawful to operate a boat towing an aquaplane within two hundred feet of any person, boat, buoy, shoreline or obstacle anywhere on the lake, except in an area designated by rules adopted by the park manager and posted. (Ord. 391 § 504, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,399,Calaveras_County.pdf,61
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.310 - Aquaplaning—Dock or beach starts.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.310 - Aquaplaning—Dock or beach starts.
It is unlawful for any person to make dock or beach starts when towing an aquaplane in areas prohibited for such purposes by rules adopted by the park manager and posted against such use. (Ord. 391 § 505, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,399,Calaveras_County.pdf,51
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.320 - Houseboats.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.320 - Houseboats.
No water craft which is utilized for human habitation may be placed or operated on any public waters or moored at a fixed or permanent mooring point without approval from the park manager. Water craft so operating and containing toilets or galleys will not use such toilets or galleys without prior written approval of the county health department. (Ord. 391 § 506, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,399,Calaveras_County.pdf,81
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.330 - Operation of boat near dam.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.330 - Operation of boat near dam.
It is unlawful to operate a boat within two hundred feet of a dam or within a border line designating the area. (Ord. 391 § 507, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,399,Calaveras_County.pdf,38
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.340 - Parking permitted only in designated areas.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.340 - Parking permitted only in designated areas.
Vehicles, including boat and house trailers, luggage trailers, automobiles, trucks and buses, shall be parked only in a designated parking area. (Ord. 391 § 600, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,400,Calaveras_County.pdf,42
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.350 - Washing articles.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.350 - Washing articles.
It is unlawful for any person to wash, rinse or otherwise clean cooking or eating utensils, food, clothing, camping equipment or other articles, in a lake, river, stream, pond, pool or other body of public waters, or at a hydrant within a recreation area, except as provided by the park manager or his authorized representative. (Ord. 391 § 601, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,400,Calaveras_County.pdf,83
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.360 - Dumping garbage.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.360 - Dumping garbage.
It is unlawful to dump, place or deposit garbage, food, manure, refuse, hay, soil, lumber, trash or rubbish in a recreation area except in receptacles designated of the purpose. (Ord. 391 § 602, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,400,Calaveras_County.pdf,54
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.370 - Camping.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.370 - Camping.
A. Camping is permitted only in areas designated by the park manager or his authorized representative. No camping is permitted without payment of fees or charges required by the owner or operator of the recreation area. B. Camping equipment, campers, house trailers, boats and boat trailers shall not be abandoned or left unattended for a period of twenty-four hours or more and may not be placed on a campsite prior to actual occupancy. C. Camping is permitted for a period of two weeks or such other period of time as the park manager may set. D. Quiet shall be maintained in all camping areas between the hours of ten p.m. and six a.m. (Ord. 628 Art. II(part), 1971: Ord. 391 § 603, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,400,Calaveras_County.pdf,159
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.380 - Vehicles in campground area.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.380 - Vehicles in campground area.
It is unlawful to operate motorbikes, motorcycles or other motor vehicles in the campground area for any purpose other than access into or egress out of an established campsite. (Ord. 628 Art. II (part), 1971: Ord. 391 § 604, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,400,Calaveras_County.pdf,63
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.390 - Noise levels.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.390 - Noise levels.
The operation or use of any audio or noise producing device including communication media and motorized equipment or vehicles in such a manner as to unreasonably annoy or endanger persons in a public place in the park is prohibited. (Ord. 628 Art. II (part), 1971: Ord. 391 § 605, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,400,Calaveras_County.pdf,71
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.400 - Minors.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.400 - Minors.
Unsupervised minors under the age of eighteen years will not be allowed to camp overnight in any recreation area unless specifically allowed pursuant to rules adopted by the park manager. (Ord. 1897 § 3, 1987: Ord. 628 Art. II (part), 1971: Ord. 391 § 606, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,401,Calaveras_County.pdf,74
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.405 - Tulloch Reservoir.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.405 - Tulloch Reservoir.
A. The following restrictions shall apply only to Tulloch Reservoir. Should a conflict exist between the regulations contained in this section and other sections of Chapter 12.20, the provisions of this section shall control. B. The following activities are restricted or prohibited on Tulloch Reservoir: 1. No person shall operate any boat in excess of forty-five miles per hour at any time on any portion of Tulloch Reservoir or, if in a restricted speed zone, in excess of five miles per hour. 2. No person shall operate any boat in excess of five miles per hour between sunset and sunrise the following day. 3. No person shall land or take off in any aircraft on any portion of Tulloch Reservoir. 4. No person shall parachute any person or object into any portion of Tulloch Reservoir. 5. No person shall operate on any portion of Tulloch Reservoir a boat towing a parasail or other type of parachute or sail capable of lifting a person or object above the surface of the reservoir. 6. All boat travel shall be in a counterclockwise direction on the lake. C. These restrictions and prohibitions shall be effective as soon as such areas are marked with appropriate signs or devices. (Ord. 1945 § 1, 1988). ",Calaveras_County,401,Calaveras_County.pdf,274
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.410 - Enforcement—Issuance of citations.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.410 - Enforcement—Issuance of citations.
In accordance with Sections 853.6 through 853.8, inclusive of the Penal Code of the state, provision is made for the issuance of citations for violations of this chapter. (Ord. 1045 § 44(a), 1978: Ord. 391 § 700, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,401,Calaveras_County.pdf,65
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.420 - Enforcement—Court appearance—Notice.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.420 - Enforcement—Court appearance—Notice.
If any person is arrested for a violation of this chapter and such person is not immediately taken before a magistrate as is more fully set forth in the Penal Code, the arresting officer shall prepare in duplicate a written notice to appear in court, containing the name and address of such person, the offense charged and the time and place where and when such person shall appear in court. (Ord. 391 § 701, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,401,Calaveras_County.pdf,88
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.430 - Enforcement—Court appearance—Time.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.430 - Enforcement—Court appearance—Time.
The time specified in the notice to appear shall be at least five days after arrest. (Ord. 391 § 702, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,401,Calaveras_County.pdf,31
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.440 - Enforcement—Court appearance—Place.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.440 - Enforcement—Court appearance—Place.
The place specified in the notice to appear shall be the court of the magistrate before whom the person would be taken if the requirement of taking an arrested person before a magistrate were complied with, or shall be an officer authorized by such court to receive a deposit of bail. (Ord. 391 § 703, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,401,Calaveras_County.pdf,67
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.450 - Enforcement—Court appearance—Promise to appear.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.450 - Enforcement—Court appearance—Promise to appear.
The arresting officer shall deliver one copy of the notice to appear to the arrested person; and the arrested person, in order to secure release, must give his written promise to appear in court by signing the duplicate notice which shall be retained by the office. Thereupon, the arresting officer shall forthwith release the person arrested from custody. (Ord. 391 § 704, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,402,Calaveras_County.pdf,80
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.460 - Enforcement—Bail and appearance.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.460 - Enforcement—Bail and appearance.
A. The officer shall, as soon as practical, file the duplicate notice with the magistrate specified therein. B. Thereupon, the magistrate shall fix the amount of bail which, in his judgment and in accordance with the provisions of Section 1275 of the Penal Code, is reasonable and sufficient of the appearance of the defendant and shall endorse upon the notice a statement signed by him in the form set forth in Section 815 (a) of the Penal Code. C. The defendant may, prior to the day upon which he promised to appear in court, deposit with the magistrate the amount of the bail thus set. D. Thereafter, at the time when the case is called for arraignment before the magistrate, if the defendant does not appear either in person or by counsel, the magistrate shall declare the bail forfeited and may, in his discretion, order that no further proceedings be had in the case. E. Upon making the order that no further proceedings be had, all sums deposited as bail shall forthwith be paid into the county treasury for distribution pursuant to Section 1463 of the Penal Code. (Ord. 391 § 705, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,402,Calaveras_County.pdf,238
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.470 - Enforcement—Warrant issuance restriction.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.470 - Enforcement—Warrant issuance restriction.
No warrants shall issue on a charge for the arrest of a person who has given a written promise to appear in court, as provided in Section 12.20.450, unless and until he has violated such promise or has failed to deposit bail, to appear for arraignment, trial or judgment, or to comply with the terms and provisions of the judgment as required by law. (Ord. 391 § 706, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,402,Calaveras_County.pdf,91
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.480 - Enforcement—Failure to appear—Penalty.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.480 - Enforcement—Failure to appear—Penalty.
Any person wilfully violating his written promise to appear in court is guilty of a misdemeanor regardless of the disposition of the charge upon which he has originally been arrested and shall be punishable by a fine of not to exceed five hundred dollars, or by imprisonment in the county jail for not to exceed six months, or both such fine and imprisonment. (Ord. 391 § 707, 1967). ",Calaveras_County,402,Calaveras_County.pdf,81
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.490 - Enforcement—Failure to appear—Issuance of warrant.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.490 - Enforcement—Failure to appear—Issuance of warrant.
When a person signs a written promise to appear at the time and place specified in the written promise to appear and has not posted bail as provided in Section 853.6 of the Penal Code of the state, the magistrate shall issue and have delivered for execution a warrant for his arrest within twenty days after his failure to appear as promised or, if such person promises to appear before an officer authorized to accept bail other than a magistrate and fails to do so on or before the date which he promised to appear, the magistrate shall issue and have directed for execution a warrant for his arrest within twenty days after the delivery of such written promise to appear by the officer to a magistrate having jurisdiction over the offense. When such person violates his promise to appear before an officer authorized to receive bail other than a magistrate, the officer shall immediately deliver to the magistrate having jurisdiction over the offense charged the written promise to appear and the complaint, if any, filed by the arresting officer. (Ord. 1045 § 44(b), 1978: Ord. 391 § 708, 1968) ",Calaveras_County,402,Calaveras_County.pdf,219
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS,12.20.500 - Enforcement—Penalty for violation.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.20 - RECREATION AREAS | 12.20.500 - Enforcement—Penalty for violation.
Any person who violates a provision of this chapter is guilty of a misdemeanor, which shall be punishable by imprisonment in the county jail for a period of not to exceed six months, or by a fine not to exceed five hundred dollars, or by both such fine and imprisonment. (Ord. 1045 § 4(c), 1978: Ord. 391 § 800, 1968) ",Calaveras_County,403,Calaveras_County.pdf,82
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 
Sections: Footnotes: --- (4) --- Prior ordinance history: Ord. 1116. ",Calaveras_County,403,Calaveras_County.pdf,21
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.010 - Title.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.010 - Title.
The ordinance codified in this chapter shall be called the ""county airport ordinance."" (Ord. 1493 (part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,403,Calaveras_County.pdf,30
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.020 - Necessity.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.020 - Necessity.
The ordinance codified in this chapter is enacted to protect the health, safety, peace, welfare and convenience of the general public using the airport and the public affected by the operation of the airport by providing for the orderly conduct of activities on and related to the airport. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,403,Calaveras_County.pdf,66
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.23.030 - De␀nitions.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.23.030 - De␀nitions.
For the purpose of this chapter, the following definitions and meanings shall apply unless otherwise specified: A. ""Aircraft"" means a device used or intended to be used for manned flight, including but not limited to airplanes, helicopters, gliders, blimps and balloons. Hang gliders are not aircraft for the purpose of this chapter. B. ""Airport"" means the Calaveras County Airport, its buildings and facilities, and all lands owned by the county contiguous to the airport, including airspace above such land. C. ""Air traffic"" means aircraft operating in the air or on an airport surface, excluding parking areas. D. ""Balloon"" means a lighter-than-air aircraft which is not engine driven. E. ""Commercial activity"" means any transfer of goods, operation or service performed for compensation which is conducted on or based at the airport. F. ""Commercial operator"" means any person involved in a commercial activity. G. ""County"" means the county of Calaveras. H. ""Director"" means the director of the county department of public works. I. ""Fixed base operator"" means any person who rents, leases or owns facilities with contiguous aircraft apron and direct access to the aircraft operation area, and who engages in an aviation-related business activity in compliance with Resolution 81-323, providing sales or services, including but not limited to the following: 1. Selling and/or servicing new and used aircraft and component parts; 2. Aircraft maintenance and repairs; 3. Sales and/or repairs of avionics; 4. Aviation training (including ground or flight instruction); 5. Aerial photography; 6. Air ambulance; 7. Aircraft agricultural operations (crop-dusting, seeding, spraying, fertilizing, etc.); 8. Aircraft rental, charter or leasing. J. ""Fueling"" means fueling or defueling of an aircraft. K. ""Manager"" means the manager of the county airport, Maury Rasmussen Field, as designated by the board of supervisors. L. ""Night"" means the period between the end of evening civil twilight and the beginning of morning civil twilight, as published in the American Air Almanac, converted to local time. M. ""Person"" means an individual, firm, partnership, corporation, company, association, joint-stock association, or governmental entity, and includes a trustee, receiver, assignee or similar representative of any of them. N. ""Traffic pattern"" means the traffic flow prescribed for aircraft landing at or taking off from the airport. O. Word Construction. The following construction applies throughout this chapter: 1. Words importing the singular include the plural; 2. Words importing the plural include the singular; 3. Words importing the masculine include the feminine. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,403,Calaveras_County.pdf,575
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.040 - Airport manager.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.040 - Airport manager.
The airport shall be under the supervision of the airport manager and the county executive officer or designee. The airport manager is appointed by the county executive officer and shall at all times have authority to take action necessary to safeguard the public and attendants at the airport and to make and enforce rules and regulations in addition to those provided in this chapter. He shall also have authority to adopt such rules and regulations as are necessary in an emergency. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). (Ord. No. 3199, § 1, 2-27-2024) ",Calaveras_County,404,Calaveras_County.pdf,120
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.050 - Public works director.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.050 - Public works director.
The public works director shall supervise the airport manager and shall have authority over the airport manager. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,405,Calaveras_County.pdf,31
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.060 - Regulations for use of the airport.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.060 - Regulations for use of the airport.
All persons using the airport shall be subject to and governed by this chapter, all county ordinances and resolutions, state and federal laws, and FAA rules and regulations. A copy of the ordinance codified in this chapter and any amendments shall be posted at the airport. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,405,Calaveras_County.pdf,65
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.070 - Aircraft—Storage and parking.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.070 - Aircraft—Storage and parking.
A. Aircraft shall be stored or parked only at places designated for storage or parking by the manager. The owner or operator of the aircraft shall be responsible for tying down and securing the aircraft. No aircraft shall be left unattended on the airport unless properly secured or in a hangar. B. Prior to storing or basing an aircraft at the airport, the owner of the aircraft to be stored or based shall register the aircraft with the manager. C. Neither the county nor the manager shall be responsible for tying down and securing the aircraft. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,405,Calaveras_County.pdf,121
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.080 - Fees and charges.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.080 - Fees and charges.
The county shall establish and maintain available for examination a schedule of fees and charges for the use of the airport and its facilities. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,405,Calaveras_County.pdf,38
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.090 - Commercial activities.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.090 - Commercial activities.
No person shall utilize the airport for commercial purposes without first obtaining a lease or permit from the county issued pursuant to Resolution 81-323. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,405,Calaveras_County.pdf,41
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.100 - Hours of operation.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.100 - Hours of operation.
Except as set forth in Section 12.28.110, the airport shall be open for use twenty-four hours a day. The airport shall be attended from nine a.m. to five p.m. daily. At other times services may be obtained by contacting the manager by telephone. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,405,Calaveras_County.pdf,70
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.110 - Repairs and maintenance.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.110 - Repairs and maintenance.
Aircraft or vehicle maintenance or repairs shall be performed only in the areas designated for such purposes by the county. Engine run-ups not incidental to takeoff or landing shall not be conducted between five p.m. and nine a.m. (Ord. 1493 (part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,405,Calaveras_County.pdf,60
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.120 - Restrictions on use of airport.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.120 - Restrictions on use of airport.
When the manager deems it necessary for the safety of the airport's users and/or nearby residents, the manager shall restrict the use of the airport or close it. Reasons for such restriction or closure may include, but are not limited to, the following: A. Weather conditions; B. The condition of the landing area; C. The presentation of special events; D. Construction or repair activity. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,406,Calaveras_County.pdf,93
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.130 - Restricted areas.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.130 - Restricted areas.
For reasons of the safety or protection of the public, the manager may close areas of the airport to the general public or restrict access thereto. No person shall enter any such closed or restricted area except persons duly authorized by the airport manager and law enforcement or firefighting personnel. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,406,Calaveras_County.pdf,68
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.140 - Access to runways.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.140 - Access to runways.
No person shall enter upon any runway or runway enclosure of the airport except when in an aircraft or with the consent of the manager. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,406,Calaveras_County.pdf,39
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.150 - Animals.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.150 - Animals.
No person shall permit any animal to enter the airport unless the animal is leashed, is in a shipping container, or is otherwise under physical restraint. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,406,Calaveras_County.pdf,43
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.160 - Starting engines.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.160 - Starting engines.
A. Aircraft engines may only be started at the airport if: 1. A qualified, competent operator is at the controls; and 2. The aircraft's brakes are in good condition and are fully applied or the wheels are securely blocked. B. No aircraft engine may be started at the airport if it is in such a position that the propeller slipstream or jet blast may damage property or injure persons. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,406,Calaveras_County.pdf,97
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.170 - Taxiing.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.170 - Taxiing.
No person shall taxi any aircraft into, out of, or within any hangar or other building on the airport. All aircraft shall be operated with due care and taxied at a safe speed not to exceed fifteen miles per hour. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,406,Calaveras_County.pdf,59
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.180 - Projectiles.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.180 - Projectiles.
No person shall shoot or throw any projectile into, on or across any portion of the airport. This section does not apply to peace officers or military personnel performing their duties as such. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,406,Calaveras_County.pdf,49
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.190 - Tra␀c pattern.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.190 - Tra␀c pattern.
Before landing and after takeoff, every aircraft shall be flown in accordance with the traffic pattern illustrated on the attached diagram labelled ""Exhibit A,"" and incorporated at the end of this chapter. Aircraft travelling faster than one hundred twenty-five miles per hour shall be flown outside the pattern shown on Exhibit A. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,407,Calaveras_County.pdf,73
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.200 - Takeo␀s and landings.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.200 - Takeo␀s and landings.
A. All initial takeoffs shall commence at the end of the runway unless cleared by the manager. B. Touch-and-go landings shall be permitted only after the pilot has received approval from the airport manager. C. Single-engine aircraft having five hundred or more horsepower are prohibited from operating at the county airport except in emergency conditions or by permission of the airport manager. D. Jet-power aircraft must have prior approval of the airport manager to land at the county airport. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,407,Calaveras_County.pdf,106
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.210 - Aircraft fueling and defueling.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.210 - Aircraft fueling and defueling.
A. No aircraft shall be fueled at the airport: 1. While the aircraft's engine is running; 2. While the aircraft is in a hangar; or 3. While the aircraft is in any other enclosed space. B. No smoking is permitted at the airport within fifty feet of an aircraft or fuel truck while an aircraft is being fueled. C. All hoses, funnels and other equipment used in fueling aircraft shall be equipped with a grounding device which shall be used to prevent static ignition of volatile liquids. D. During fueling, no person shall operate a radio transmitter or receiver, nor switch on or off any electric or electronic equipment in the aircraft or within fifty feet of the aircraft. E. If a fuel spill or leak occurs, no person shall start the engine of any aircraft within fifty feet of the spill until such time as the fuel has been cleaned. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,407,Calaveras_County.pdf,192
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.220 - Liability insurance.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.220 - Liability insurance.
Each aircraft based at the airport shall be covered by liability insurance in the following minimum amounts: A. Personal injury, one hundred thousand dollars per person, three hundred thousand dollars per incident; B. Property damage, one hundred thousand dollars. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,407,Calaveras_County.pdf,60
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.230 - Defective or unsafe aircraft.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.230 - Defective or unsafe aircraft.
No person shall land, take off, taxi or operate any aircraft at the airport which is not operating properly, or is equipped with any part or safety device which is apparently defective and renders the aircraft unsafe to operate. The manager shall determine whether an aircraft is unsafe to operate. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,407,Calaveras_County.pdf,68
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.240 - Aerobatics prohibited.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.240 - Aerobatics prohibited.
No person shall perform any aerobatics or stunt maneuver over or within one mile of the airport. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,408,Calaveras_County.pdf,33
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.250 - Sale of goods.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.250 - Sale of goods.
No person shall sell any goods or merchandise or any services at the airport without obtaining the manager's consent. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,408,Calaveras_County.pdf,34
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.260 - Accidents.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.260 - Accidents.
A. Every person involved in an aircraft accident on the airport shall promptly report such accident to the manager and the federal and state agencies to which he is required to report by law or regulation. B. The owner and the operator of an aircraft damaged in an accident shall be responsible for the prompt removal of the aircraft from the airport. If the operator and the owner do not remove the damaged aircraft, the manager shall remove the aircraft at the owner's and the operator's expense. The manager shall not be responsible for any damage to the aircraft if he must so remove it. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,408,Calaveras_County.pdf,127
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.270 - Fire prevention.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.270 - Fire prevention.
A. No person shall smoke within any hangar, fuel-handling area or storage area, in any aircraft parking area, or inside or within fifty feet of any aircraft. B. No person may use flammable liquids to clean any aircraft, or part thereof, in any hangar or building except buildings approved therefor by the manager after inspecting the ventilation, fireproofing and fire-extinguishing equipment. C. No person shall light or use any open flame in any hangar or other building on the airport without the manager's prior consent. D. No person shall operate electric or gas welding or cutting equipment on the airport without the manager's prior consent. E. No person shall store or discard any flammable liquid, gas, flare, or other flammable material at the airport except in such areas designated therefor by the manager. F. Oily waste, rags and other combustible waste shall be disposed of in metal containers with metal lids. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,408,Calaveras_County.pdf,207
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.280 - Fuel sales.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.280 - Fuel sales.
No person shall deliver aviation fuels or lubricants to the airport without the county's consent. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,408,Calaveras_County.pdf,31
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.290 - Restriction or closure of airport.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.290 - Restriction or closure of airport.
A. The manager may close the airport, or a portion thereof, or restrict operations thereon if he determines that such closure or restriction is necessary to protect the safety and welfare of airport users and nearby residents. Reasons for such closure include, but are not limited to, the following: 1. Weather conditions; 2. The condition of the landing area; 3. Maintenance or repair of runway; 4. Obstacles on the runway; 5. Fire; 6. Aircraft accident; 7. Special events. B. To close the airport, the manager must place an ""X"" at each end of the runway to be closed, the arms of which are at least sixteen feet long and two feet wide. The ""X"" shall be colored so as to contrast with the surface on which it is placed. The manager shall immediately notify the Stockton Flight Service Station or local FAA facility and issue a notice to airmen advising of the closure of the airport. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,409,Calaveras_County.pdf,212
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.300 - Vehicle operations.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.300 - Vehicle operations.
All drivers of vehicles, excluding aircraft, shall observe the following rules during vehicular operation: A. Vehicles shall yield the right-of-way to aircraft. B. Vehicles operating on the runways or taxiways shall be painted, marked and lighted as directed by the manager, or shall display an orange and white checkered flag not less than three feet square. C. No person shall operate any motor vehicle at the airport over fifteen miles per hour, except operators of emergency vehicles responding to an emergency. The speed limit for vehicles in aircraft parking lots and on the apron shall be a maximum of fifteen miles per hour. D. Vehicles may only be parked in areas posted therefor or in a rented tiedown space. E. Vehicles shall not be driven on runways, taxiways, aircraft parking areas or aprons without obtaining the manager's consent. F. The airport manager may designate parking areas by posting signs. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). ",Calaveras_County,409,Calaveras_County.pdf,197
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT,12.28.305 - Regulations for use of the airport.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.28 - COUNTY AIRPORT | 12.28.305 - Regulations for use of the airport.
A. No person shall use any portion of the airport, including but not limited to any hangars or parking spaces thereon, in any manner whatsoever for any commercial profit, gainful or revenue-producing purposes, including, but not limited to, flight instruction or mechanical work, or any charitable purpose without the written approval of the county. Such written approval, by lease or otherwise, shall be granted only pursuant to standards and regulations established by resolution of the board. B. The county may restrict the number of persons using the airport to such number as the county may deem necessary to protect the public health, safety and welfare. (Ord. 1493(part), 1982). EXHIBIT ""A"" ",Calaveras_County,409,Calaveras_County.pdf,144
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS,,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS | 
Sections: ",Calaveras_County,410,Calaveras_County.pdf,3
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS,12.32.010 - Purpose.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS | 12.32.010 - Purpose.
In order to protect the due process rights, private property rights, economy, resources and economic stability of the county and its citizens, it is critical that federal and state agencies and other non-Calaveras County governmental agencies recognize and address the effects of any actions proposed within the county or concerning the land, private or public, within the county. (Ord. 2439 § 2(part), 1995). ",Calaveras_County,410,Calaveras_County.pdf,84
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS,12.32.020 - Findings and declarations.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS | 12.32.020 - Findings and declarations.
The board of supervisors finds and declares: A. The board of supervisors of the county is concerned in the extreme about the adverse impacts on the economy, privat rights, resources, and land use within the county arising from certain regulatory and administrative practices by federa agencies and other non-Calaveras County governmental agencies in recent years. B. Federal and state agencies and other non-Calaveras County governmental agencies have a legal and enforceable duty to observe the limitations placed on such agencies by the U.S. and California Constitutions, including but not limited to, the taking of private property and private property interests for public use without just compensation in violation of the Fifth and Fourteenth Amendments of the U.S. Constitution, and the violation of the rights, privileges and protections guaranteed to the citizens of Calaveras County by the U.S. Constitution and the federal and state Civil Rights Acts. (Ord. 2439 § 2(part), 1995). ",Calaveras_County,410,Calaveras_County.pdf,192
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS,12.32.030 - Federal and state agencies and other non-Calaveras County governmental agencies noti␀ed.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS | 12.32.030 - Federal and state agencies and other non-Calaveras County governmental agencies noti␀ed.
Federal and state agencies and other non-Calaveras County governmental agencies are herewith notified that the county and its citizens expect and require that federal and state officers and employees observe the limitations of the U.S. and California Constitutions on governmental actions and that federal and state officers and employees follow the laws and regulations governing the agencies that guarantee to the citizens and property owners of Calaveras County due process, economic stability, public health, safety, local land use, and conservation of natural resources and the environment of the county, including its agricultural industry, livestock grazing, water resources, mining of gold and other mineral resources, and outdoor recreation in scenic natural settings. (Ord. 2439 § 2(part), 1995). ",Calaveras_County,411,Calaveras_County.pdf,147
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS,12.32.040 - Federal and state agencies and other non-Calaveras County governmental agencies to coordinate.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS | 12.32.040 - Federal and state agencies and other non-Calaveras County governmental agencies to coordinate.
The Calaveras County board of supervisors now call upon the federal and state management agencies to coordinate in advance with the board any proposed actions which will impact either the federal or state managed lands in Calaveras County, the private property rights, or the economic stability and historically developed custom and culture of the county. To the extent required or permitted by law, such management agencies are required to so coordinate their actions by obtaining board approval, prior to taking official action. A. The Calaveras County board of supervisors shall be consulted in accordance with the laws and regulations of the state of California and the United States regarding any pending, contemplated or proposed actions affecting local communities and citizens of the county. B. All federal and state agencies and other non-Calaveras County government agencies shall, to the fullest extent permissible by law, comply with all applicable policies and procedures issued by the county. C. Federal and state agencies and other non-Calaveras County governmental agencies shall inform the county, or its designee(s), of all pending, contemplated or proposed actions affecting local communities, citizens, or affecting county policy. Such notification shall include the regulatory authority and statutory procedure for the action, a detailed description of the proposed action, plan, procedure, rule, guideline or amendment sufficient to fully inform lay persons of its intent and effects of the resources, environment, private property interests, and economic stability of the county. D. When required by law or when requested by the county, all federal and state agencies and other non-Calaveras County governmental agencies proposing actions that may impact citizens of the county shall prepare and submit in writing, and in timely manner as soon as is reasonable, report(s) on the purposes, objectives and estimated impacts of such actions, including environmental, health, safety, private property, and economic impacts, to the county and its citizens. Those reports shall be provided to the county for review and coordination with sufficient lead time for the county to prepare a meaningful response for consideration by the federal or state agency. (Ord. 2439 § 2(part), 1995). ",Calaveras_County,411,Calaveras_County.pdf,418
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS,12.32.050 - Public hearings.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS | 12.32.050 - Public hearings.
When a public hearing is required by law or when requested by the county, all federal and state agencies and other non- Calaveras County governmental agencies proposing actions that may impact citizens of the county shall hold the public hearing with the board of supervisors, unless the board declines. If the agency proposes multiple hearings within the county, the last of the hearings shall be with the board of supervisors. (Ord. 2439 § 2(part), 1995). ",Calaveras_County,412,Calaveras_County.pdf,94
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS,12.32.060 - Environmental review.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS | 12.32.060 - Environmental review.
Before federal and state agencies and other non-Calaveras County governmental agencies take or adversely affect private property interests or alter land use(s), environmental review of the proposed action shall be conducted by the lead agency, and mitigation measures adopted in accordance with policies, practices and procedures applicable to the proposed action and in accordance with all applicable federal, state and local laws. Impact studies shall, as needed, address the effects on community and economic resources, the environment, public health, safety and welfare, private property, grazing rights, mining rights, flood- prone areas and access and any other relevant impacts. (Ord. 2439 § 2(part), 1995). ",Calaveras_County,412,Calaveras_County.pdf,134
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS,12.32.070 - Noticing and review procedures.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS | 12.32.070 - Noticing and review procedures.
A. For the purpose of this chapter, each federal and state agency shall, unless specifically authorized otherwise: 1. Give the required notice(s) to the county and the board of supervisors via certified mail as follows: Clerk of the Calaveras County Board of Supervisors Government Center, 891 Mountain Ranch Road San Andreas, CA 95249 2. Not less than ten complete copies of the written documents supporting the proposed action shall be provided to the clerk of the board of supervisors at the above-referenced address in order that members of the board of supervisors, county staff and the public shall have an opportunity to review and consider the documents. 3. These documents shall be available for public review at the above-referenced location. 4. Notification of the availability of related documents shall be available for the minimum time set forth by the federal and state statute for such review or, if none is established by law, for a period of not less than forty-five days prior to the proposed date of action, adoption or approval. This time is necessary to ensure adequate local opportunity for consideration and response. B. Upon receipt of such notification and documents, the clerk of the board shall list the notification and related materials on the next board of supervisors public agenda correspondence list. This list shall be available at the clerk of the board's office, Government Center, 891 Mountain Ranch Road, San Andreas, CA 95249. C. While this is not considered exclusive, the clerk of this board shall cause a copy of the ordinance codified in this chapter to be forwarded to the following agencies: 1. U.S. Corps of Engineers; 2. U.S. Department of Fish and Wildlife; 3. U.S. Department of Agriculture, Forest Services; 4. U.S. Department of Interior, Bureau of Land Management; 5. U.S. Department of Interior, Bureau of Reclamation; 6. California Department of Fish and Game; 7. California Department of Forestry and Fire Protection; 8. California Department of Parks and Recreation; 9. California Department of Transportation; 10. East Bay Municipal Water District. D. The board of supervisors may designate one or more members of its staff, and/or one or more citizens, to receive, review and comment upon any pending, contemplated or proposed action of any federal or state agency, or any related information and may request such designee(s) report to the board. (Ord. 2439 § 2(part), 1995). ",Calaveras_County,412,Calaveras_County.pdf,512
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS,12.32.080 - Citizen claims.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS | 12.32.080 - Citizen claims.
Any citizen or group claiming to be affected by any pending, contemplated or proposed action of any federal or state agency where a decision or comment upon such action is within the subject matter jurisdiction of the board of supervisors is encouraged to present relevant information to the board. The board shall consider such information and, where appropriate, shall convey such information to the particular federal or state agency for consideration as an official statement(s) of the city. (Ord. 2439 § 2(part), 1995). ",Calaveras_County,413,Calaveras_County.pdf,101
"Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES",Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS,12.32.090 - Validity.,"Calaveras_County | Title 12 - STREETS, SIDEWALKS AND PUBLIC PLACES | Chapter 12.32 - STATE AND FEDERAL PUBLIC LANDS | 12.32.090 - Validity.
If any part of the ordinance codified in this chapter shall be held void by a court of competent jurisdiction, such part shall be deemed severable, and the invalidity thereof shall not affect the remaining parts of the ordinance codified in this chapter. (Ord. 2439 § 2(part), 1995). ",Calaveras_County,413,Calaveras_County.pdf,66
