Title 15 - BUILDINGS AND CONSTRUCTION,Chapter 15.05 - GRADING AND DRAINAGE ORDINANCE,15.06.032 - Basis for establishing the areas of special ␀ood hazard.,"Calaveras_County | Title 15 - BUILDINGS AND CONSTRUCTION | Chapter 15.05 - GRADING AND DRAINAGE ORDINANCE | 15.06.032 - Basis for establishing the areas of special ␀ood hazard.
The areas of special flood hazard identified by the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) in the ""Flood Insurance Study (FIS) for Calaveras County Unincorporated Areas"" dated September 5, 1990, with accompanying Flood Insurance Rate Maps (FIRMs) and Flood Boundary and Floodway Maps (FBFMs), dated September 5, 1990, supplemented and updated by Base Flood Elevations determined from the Atkins Study (an automated limited detailed floodplain study performed for and reviewed for Quality Assurance/Quality Control by FEMA in 2016), and all subsequent amendments and/or revisions, are hereby adopted by reference and declared to be a part of this chapter. This Flood Insurance Study and attendant mapping is the minimum area of applicability of this chapter and may be supplemented by studies for other areas which allow implementation of this chapter and which are recommended to the board of supervisors by the floodplain administrator. The study, FIRMs and FBFMs are on file at the Calaveras County Planning Department, Government Center, 891 Mountain Ranch Road, in San Andreas, California. (Ord. No. 2955, 8-19-2008; Ord. No. 3084, § 2, 5-23-2017) ",Calaveras_County,461,Calaveras_County.pdf,262
