Title 17 - ZONING,Chapter 17.12 - Parcel Size Limitation (X) Overlay Zone,17.12.010 - Purpose.,"Calaveras_County | Title 17 - ZONING | Chapter 17.12 - Parcel Size Limitation (X) Overlay Zone | 17.12.010 - Purpose.
The purpose of the parcel size limitation (X) overlay zone is to identify specific areas where minimum parcel size for a specific parcel is different than that of the zoning district in which the parcel is located. ",Calaveras_County,597,Calaveras_County.pdf,41
Title 17 - ZONING,Chapter 17.12 - Parcel Size Limitation (X) Overlay Zone,17.12.020 - Applicability.,"Calaveras_County | Title 17 - ZONING | Chapter 17.12 - Parcel Size Limitation (X) Overlay Zone | 17.12.020 - Applicability.
The X overlay zone shall be applied to parcels subject to a specific parcel size limitation and prohibited from future subdivision. The X overlay zone may be used to identify the following: A. Density Transfer. Parcels for which the density has been transferred as a part of a planned unit development to other parcels. B. Common Area. Common area parcels that are a part of a planned unit development or subdivision map. C. Other. Parcels established for the purpose of mitigating or protecting biological, cultural, or other resources as a part of a planned development or subdivision map that is not intended to be further developed. ",Calaveras_County,597,Calaveras_County.pdf,125
