Title 17 - ZONING,Chapter 17.42 - Use Classi␀cations,"17.43.250 - ""Y"" Terms.","Calaveras_County | Title 17 - ZONING | Chapter 17.42 - Use Classi␀cations | 17.43.250 - ""Y"" Terms.
A. Yard. The area between the property line and the nearest wall of the first main building on a lot. 1. Front Yard. A yard extending across the front of a lot for the full width of the lot between the side lot lines. 2. Interior Yard. A yard which does not abut a street. 3. Rear Yard. A yard extending across the rear of a lot for its full width between side lot lines. 4. Side Yard. A yard extending from the rear line of the front yard to the front line of the rear yard. 5. Street Side Yard. A yard on a corner lot along a street side lot line extending from the rear line of the front yard to the rear lot line. FIGURE 17.43.250.A: YARD TYPES ",Calaveras_County,776,Calaveras_County.pdf,165
Title 17 - ZONING,Chapter 17.42 - Use Classi␀cations,"17.43.260 - ""Z"" Terms.","Calaveras_County | Title 17 - ZONING | Chapter 17.42 - Use Classi␀cations | 17.43.260 - ""Z"" Terms.
A. Zone. See ""Zoning District"". B. Zoning District. A specifically delineated area in the county within which regulations and requirements uniformly govern the use, placement, spacing, and size of land and buildings. ",Calaveras_County,776,Calaveras_County.pdf,46
